(1, 'effects-of-corona-virus-on-the-stock-market-2020-vs-2021', 'Thu, 04 Mar 2021 20:40:26 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the upsurge in the rate of those affected by the Corona pandemic, not only did we witness a state of chaos in people but a substantial increase in the frequency of casualties all across the globe due to its rapid spread. The world experienced a global recession with a great shift in stock markets due to the lockdown implementation. This left millions unemployed (almost 400 million according to International Labour Organization; 8.9% in the US according to the IMF), instigated a 10% reduction in the overall incomes globally, causing a loss equivalent to US$3.5 trillion, and many small-scale businesses eventually closing down. This resulted in a significant revenue boost of $3.9 trillion globally to all the businesses that operated online because, in the long run, there were as high as 67% of the customers who decided not to travel any more than a 5 km radius from their homes for shopping. While every economy more or less suffered the effects, the only one that seemed to flourish in this hard time was China’s, with a growth recorded to be 2.3%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":143,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/corona-5073359_1920-1024x467.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-143\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Did the stock exchange really getting affected by the Corona Pandemic?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Despite the ravaging repercussions of the Coronavirus, the stock markets have been buoyant, as stated by Paul Krugman in the New York Times; “Whenever you consider the economic implications of stock prices, you want to remember three rules. First, the stock market is not the economy. Second, the stock market is not the economy. Third, the stock market is not the economy (…). The relationship between stock performance – largely driven by the oscillation between greed and fear – and real economic growth has always been somewhere between loose and nonexistent”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2021- Will the New Year bring any improvements after the catastrophic downfall?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the Financial Times Stock Exchange Index, 14.3% drop was recorded in the preliminary months of the year 2020 but it is regaining its ground quite rapidly, with the highest record in all indexes by the end of last year, e.g. a 43.7% increase in The Nasdaq, 15.6% by S&amp;P 500 and 6.6% in the Dow Jones. A global economy decline was recorded by The IMF in the overall economy in 2020, estimated to be truncated by a percentage of 4.4- with effects so drastic that it crashed in the month of March 2020. However, global growth in the overall economy of almost 5.2% is predicted to be achieved in the year 2021, with the most progress percentage by India at 8.8% and China at 8.2%, whereas a slow recovery is expected by UK and Italy, considering the fact that they got hit the worst.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that the companies are getting back on track and recovering from the ramifications and limitations of Covid-19, the global stock exchange market estimated that from around $1075.06 billion in 2020, it is expected to flourish to $1249.4 billion in the year 2021, resulting in a 16.2% escalation in the CAGR values. These values are projected to stretch to a $1738.26 billion high by the year 2025, at a 9% CAGR.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verdict</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first and foremost fact that you need to realize is that the coronavirus is not going to suddenly diminish because with each passing day new strains of the virus are evolving, making it more resilient, so we need to find ways around the problem in order to achieve our goals. Secondly, a person can only survive for a definite period of time before his treasure finally becomes empty, hence it is obligatory to realize that inflation is bound to hit the countries, making the stronger parties strongest and leaving the weakest vulnerable. Daniel J. Laginess at Creative Financial Solutions elucidates the situation by stating that “There will be a dial-back from stocks that have benefited from Covid-19 because they may be viewed as overvalued, such as work-from-home companies and home gym companies”, hence we need to focus our interests in the industries that are definitely going to grow, irrespective of the pandemic, like biotechnology, tech companies, and e-commerce, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Effects of Corona virus on the Stock Market - 2020 vs. 2021', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Uncategorized', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(2, 'us-presidency-and-stock-market', 'Fri, 05 Mar 2021 10:47:30 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Year 2020 was a different and difficult year for not only the US but for the entire world in terms of financial and economic challenges. The global financial markets took a plunge and stocks markets either remain stagnant or observed bearish trends globally. US economy was specifically impacted not only because of Covid-19 but also by the presidential elections. It is a fact that in US, the presidents are blamed and are given credit as well for the stocks market performance.  Because, they enforce the laws and policies which affect the stock market regulations and control businesses’. The victory of Joe Biden’s over Donald Trump released some pressure from the markets which were on edge pre-elections; as his trade policies are predictable and multilateral. This has greatly encouraged the investors and exporters to pool in more USD in the financial and stock markets of the US.  Also, this will have a positive impact on the monetary front of the economy in the longer run. An easier monetary policy is definitely going to benefit the overall financial and stock markets where; the yield gaps are higher, current account deficit is lower and the bond market is sensitive historically. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":150,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/usa-5958092_1920-1024x642.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-150\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Biden’s Policy Impact on Financial Market of US in 2021</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The US stock market loved the selection of Joe Biden as their president. The s&amp; p Index climbed by 14.3% from Nov 3 to January 2021 which is a record. It cooled down later because of the prevailing uncertainty due to Corona related lockdowns.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Biden’s government vowed to take the challenges imposed by the lockdowns and uncertainty. The first and foremost challenge the Biden’s government had to deal with is the Covid-19. He has planned to invest almost $25 billion in the manufacturing and distribution of the vaccine and a relief package of $1.9 trillion to escalate the growth. This is going to positively impact the US sourcing and manufacturing capabilities and in return the economy is expected to flourish so it will lower the US dependency on others.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is also a fact that the socks market will also have bullish business trends as this vaccine has a huge market internationally. It is believed that under the presidency of the Biden, the economic outlook of the US is going to be changed globally. Let me explain how; the government planned to announce tax-cuts as a key measure to mitigate the recession induced by the Corona virus which will boost the domestic stock market.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verdict:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The administrative policies have a strong influence on the stocks market performance.  there is no doubt that the policies and plans of Joe Biden have boosted the stock market and are expected to escalate economic growth in future.  However, it is also worth mentioning that these stimulus plans are not risk free. As stock market gains can be dented because of the inflation and high interest rates. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'US Presidency and Stock Market', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Uncategorized', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(3, 'have-you-filed-your-income-tax-returns-yet', 'Mon, 08 Mar 2021 14:11:28 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the announcement made by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS), the process of application and processing for the tax returns of the year 2020 has already commenced from Friday- February 12<sup>th</sup>’ 21, and its proclaimed <strong>final deadline is April 15<sup>th</sup>’ 21.</strong> Therefore, as an honest citizen, it is your due responsibility to file tax returns for the income generated in your name. If you are wondering whether or not you should be filing one – that too in the current Covid situation, here are a few things you need to know so as to decide what needs to be done and how:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":155,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/scott-graham-OQMZwNd3ThU-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-155\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>What is income tax and why it is important to file it?</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For every expense that you make, you probably always get to see an amount deducted in the name of tax on the receipts. This amount is a way of allowing the government to keep your sources of income, expenses, businesses, capital, profits, and all financial information in check through local tax agencies. The process for someone to file tax returns starts with the taxpayer filling in various forms that report his assets through which calculation of your net worth is done. This helps in identifying the amount of money he owes in taxes, overpayment of which can be refunded to the taxpayer later on, or accommodated in the next year’s tax returns.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":2} -->\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>Whether or not you are eligible to file for a tax return?</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While a lot has changed because of the Coronavirus situation, but you must know that you\'re off the hook from paying the taxes! You are eligible to file a tax return if you are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Single individuals:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>&lt;65 of age and making $12,400 annually</li><li>&gt;=65 of age with a minimum income of $14,050.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Married couple</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Both individuals &lt;65 of age, will have to file together</li><li>Both individuals =65 of age with $24,800.&nbsp;</li><li>Both individuals &gt;65 of age making $27,400 annually</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":3} -->\n<ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>Procedure for filing and paying your income tax return?&nbsp;</strong></li><li>Get all of your tax transcripts for your income retained by the IRS throughout the year. This includes:</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Transcript for your Tax returns</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Tax account transcript</li><li>Transcript of your Salary</li><li>Record of account transcript</li><li>Letter for the confirmation of non-filing</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":2} -->\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>Filing a tax return</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This starts with the collection of all of your tax filing documents from all the previous years, and fill out the forms to file the tax returns. This will help you access if you owe any money that needs to be paid by you, or refunded by the IRS. You can ask CPA to help you fill in the forms to ensure correct inputs, carefully catering to each exemption and deduction.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":3} -->\n<ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>Paying the tax return</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In case after filing your tax return, it is established that you owe more for more than your affordability, you can seek help from the IRS as they will support you through an appropriate payment plan.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":4} -->\n<ol start=\"4\"><li><strong>Tips for speedy tax filing in the current Covid situation?</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to ease the tax filing convenient for you and help you avoid any paper-processing delays in the Covid situation with minimal face-to-face encounter, the IRS has insisted people follow the following steps to make the return of refunds more efficient:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>File your income taxes electronically</li><li>Make use of direct deposit so that you can get speedy refunds</li><li>Always visit the IRS official website to stay updated with the latest news related to tax, especially associated with the Economic Impact Payments</li><li>&nbsp;Individuals entitled to stimulus payments should evaluate the Recovery Rebate Credit guidelines</li><li>A wide majority automatically received their Economic Impact Payments, which are not to be included when they file. Those eligible for the payment or not getting paid can file a claim in their tax return.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember to file your taxes in due time so that you can continue living a safe and happy life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Have you filed your Income Tax Returns yet?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Tax Returns', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(4, 'why-has-us-stock-market-been-plummeting-for-the-last-three-days', 'Mon, 08 Mar 2021 14:44:06 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The US Stock Exchange started slipping this Thursday and has since been through major troughs for three consecutive days now due to the Federal chairperson’s (Jerome H. Powell) reaction to the fear of inflation in regards to the recent long-term upsurge in the interest rates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":160,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sigmund-R401qwThw7w-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-160\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The reason behind the sudden decline in the Stock Market:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Mr. Powell gave out the speech, he prominently sidestepped from answering the question and ceased to push back against the spike in the government bond yields, resulting in the initiation of decline in the stock index leaving all the progress it had made since February 2020, after pandemic struck, go down the drain. This caused the day to culminate with a 1.55% loss of The Nasdaq Composite Index, hitting the lowest with 3% waning. The Federal Reserve Chair asked the investors not to worry and to keep bond purchasing practice continuation intact, emphasized that he would get concerned if the economic growth got affected negatively because of the increment; “I would be concerned by disorderly conditions in markets or a persistent tightening of financial conditions that threaten the achievement of our goals, I would be concerned if those things were to happen.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Trends of US Stock Market- Effect on Asian shares and Gold prices:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The investors are outraged and sternly disappointed over Mr. Powell’s reaction, leading to a drastic effect on the Stock market;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Nasdaq Composite Index has been the unfortunate of all, hitting a fall of 2.1% in market closing at 275 points loss at 12,723.47</li><li>The tech-rich S&amp;P S&amp;P 500 down 1.3%, 46 points at 3,768.47</li><li>The Dow Jones declining 1.1%, 346 points at 30,924.14</li><li>The downfall in the three major indices of the US Stock market affected the Asian Shares as</li><li>Australian stocks fell 1%</li><li>Japan\'s Nikkei share lost 0.7%</li><li>Seoul shares dropped 0.24%</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>The value of Gold collapsed to a new low</strong> with 0.2% to $1,693.79 per ounce- the lowest it last hit was in June last year at $1,688.96.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br /><strong>Why are the bond yields that big of a deal?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bond yields are important because they allow us to observe the way of looking at the economy through the investor’s perspective i.e. yields are higher when the economy is stronger resulting in higher returns, henceforth making it captivating for the investors. While the investors pushed the boundaries to bid higher yields this past year, the smaller technology stocks with low profits suffer the most due to the increase in rates. While the past has seen higher inflation connecting dots to major growth trends, the Fed seems to have taken a great risk by enacting extreme measures by raising the interest rates to push the economic growth post-pandemic. Despite the obliteration of the pandemic, the stocks kept surviving because of the zero-interest policy in March 2020, to which Mr. Powell anchored to the Fed’s pledge said that “I expect that we will be patient” even if prices increase as anticipated this spring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Why has US Stock Market been plummeting for the last three days?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Stockwatch', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(5, 'the-rise-and-fall-of-xau-what-can-we-expect', 'Mon, 08 Mar 2021 14:52:00 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The yellow metal has been walking at the edge of the mountain since a long time now and last week, it finally took a wrong step and came crashing down like a helpless climber stuck in the middle of nowhere. After reaching its highest peak, $2090 (in August), Gold has now turned 180 degrees and is aiming towards the bottom. The trend is clearly dominated by the bears and it seems like bulls will have to give up sooner or later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img width=\"624\" height=\"309\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/lPrCsnEHOjWnyIHxTs4jJ_0spgU9Cf5v_zmXBtuV75KLzlMMjj6gE8v7hgm16y6-PDBnaABkA9fJI64Kvs5KuTp6S-wd-l-TKLJw8lPFpu2Id63HhW-YbISU5VAO54GtM-bteZc\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the bulls have been trying to provide a solid support to Gold after it entered the $1600 levels, it was the bears that took complete control and stole the victory from the bulls. The last 3 weeks have been a nightmare for Gold. In the first week, it dropped by 2.5% followed by a 2.7% decline in the 2<sup>nd</sup> week and now a further 1.5% decline at the end of the 3<sup>rd</sup> week. Even though it seems like an improvement from -2.7% to -1.5%, the reality is quite the opposite.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How analysts see Gold in future</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Analysts have been working day and night to predict an accurate future trend for XAU and it is not surprising to note that most predictions point towards a pessimistic future. Eric Scoles, a well-known analyst, has predicted a sudden rise in the Gold price followed by sharp decline. He explains this as an opportunity to sell which means that once again a long-term, bearish trend is expected.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand, Przemysław Radomski (CFA), another analyst described this bearish trend as an opportunity for bulls. Radomski pointed out that Gold had reached its 61.8% Fibonacci retracement level but it has still not reached its lowest levels when compared to the previous year. According to Radomski, a bullish trend is near and soon Gold would be flying high.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But what exactly is going to happen in the next few weeks? Will Gold break through the resistance levels and reach a new record high price or will bull support fail to protect it? Let’s have a look at it in detail.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Gold and It’s Future&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After analyzing the graphs and keeping certain developments in consideration, we have prepared a hypothesis that will help you in decision making. Right now XAU seems to be going down further and it might even test the $1500 levels. With an increase in the Bitcoin value, experts have been considering it as a perfect Gold alternate. According to Bloomberg, Bitcoin has been attracting a huge portion of funds that was being consumed by Gold, stock and bonds previously. Bitcoin is expected to touch $100000 level which would be a death warrant for gold and other commodities but having said that, the trend seems to be much more complicated than this.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Gold is expected to decline further over the next few weeks, it is important to note that few indicators have been hinting towards an oversold phenomenon. While 3 out of 12 indicators favor buying, the rest of the 9 indicators of moving averages favor selling in the current scenario. As for investors, the bearish Gold journey has not yet come to an end. The yellow king will fall further towards the $1500 levels before a correction trend would appear. That will be the time to open long positions and take advantage of the new trend.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gold is in serious trouble right now but hopefully it will fight back sooner or later and take back its bullish positions in the longer run. Till then, keep visiting our website for more valuable information and let us know what you think in the comments section below!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The rise and fall of XAU – What can we expect?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Stockwatch', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(6, 'yellow-metal-hits-the-headlines', 'Tue, 16 Mar 2021 08:33:34 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pandemic that hit in the year 2019 caused the gold prices to soar up to 25% in global markets which resulted in the highest price record set for the yellow metal for the year 2020. This sudden and sharp spike in gold prices is said to be the highest annual gain in the last 10 years. Those who invested in gold and hoarded the yellow metal in the March of 2020 have been lucky and riding the high horses right now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why Invest in Gold when its prices are already sky-high?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":176,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/jingming-pan-Y9U4XZYbSQ4-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-176\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Forecast</strong> - According to analysts, Gold may continue to be an attractive investment for the upcoming year i.e. 2021 as prices might still go up for a few years. The data provided by the World Gold Council (WGC) indicated the increase in Gold prices from $1360.25 per ounce (recorded in the year 2018) to $2067 per ounce in the year 2020, suggesting further growth in the upcoming years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The decline in USD value </strong>- Analysts also expect USD to decline further which will, in turn, benefit the gold market. How you may say? Well, a weaker USD translates to few consumers of this asset such as those who stock it up and exporters, who depend on the US demand to help their businesses flourish extensively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Policies of central banks</strong> - Covid-19 forced the countries to go into lockdown and took the businesses with it. Investors’ hopes surged a little with the news of the vaccine but quickly went down the drain as the second wave of coronavirus hit the world hard, thus causing a rise in travel bans. But gold industry continued to flourish and gathered everyone’s attention across the world, which has only been possible due to the accommodative policies of the banks all over the world to make sure it doesn’t come to a standstill.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Expert Opinion: </strong>In a report published in December 2020, Nick Herbert and Patrick Collier of Credit Suisse explained that “Any near-term pullback in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.business-standard.com/topic/gold-prices\">gold prices&nbsp;</a>due to Covid-19 vaccine approvals and the rollout is a good entry point because the economy remains fragile and the post-pandemic recovery will be gradual at best, meaning a low rate environment and an elevated gold price environment is here to stay at least for the next few years. Risks to our view are a quicker-than-expected US economic recovery, a more hawkish US Fed, and lingering weakness in retail demand for gold”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verdict:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One must keep himself aware of the latest trends prevalent in the market as the developments vary each day, leading to elevation or downfall in stock prices. Therefore, you can only out-perform others by keeping a close eye on the businesses operating in a market with growth potential. Seek the opportunity and start taking risks for investment in different domains instead of dumping all of your money in a single business, so as to diversify your assets. Gold value did see a setback in the past few months but according to the experts of the field, this temporary fall in the gold prices shouldn’t scare the investments, rather this situation is to be seen as an opportunity to invest more as the prices will go back up and just in a matter of years, it would surely be worth a lot more than what it is priced at right now. Hence, investing in gold is never a bad option and will surely do more good than harm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Yellow Metal hits the headlines!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Don\'t Miss,Gold,Investment', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(7, 'meghan-and-harry-s-interview-their-most-hinted-financial-strategies', 'Tue, 16 Mar 2021 08:38:01 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the top hottest news trending for the past few days is Oprah interviewing Duke and Duchess of Sussex; Prince Harry and Meghan Markle that gave an insight into the couple’s personal affairs, and how they have been getting affected by the royal family and its traditions? The main highlight, however, that touched the audience most and gathered maximum attention was the comments on racism that the couple has to bear causing major mental stress and tormenting they had to undergo due to the comments made by the ruthless British press.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Duchess of Sussex has been a part of the news since it was announced that Prince Harry will be tying a knot with Meghan Markle. The British tabloid had since then started laying their interests in all affairs related to her, and the couple mainly due to the fact that she was considered an outsider after marriage and went through a hard time being accepted by the royal house. The reasons behind such behavior were clearly pertained to her being a mixed-race individual, a divorcee, and older than Price Harry. But, the <strong>2-hour interview</strong> <strong>aired on ITV</strong> spread like fire, with a viewership of <strong>12 million people,</strong> just on the first night it was broadcasted, on Monday night; trending as the hottest news on social media and all over the globe. While the couple got immense support from all around the world on one hand, conversely, there were many rumors of the interview being staged and Meghan proclaimed dishonesty and interview as her act for trying to seek the public’s attention. The interview gained so much popularity among people from all walks of life that Hillary Clinton- Former US Secretary of State remarked; \"This young woman was not about to keep her head down, you know, this is 2021.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":182,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/roberto-catarinicchia-qczTpxlPqPc-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-182\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Public’s opinion on Meghan Markle:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A poll with 4656 participants was conducted by YouGov; according to which 32% of the people believed that Prince Harry and the Duchess were treated fairly by the royal family, the same percentage of people believed that they were treated unfairly, while the rest 36% individuals had nothing to comment about their situation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The main features of the interview are highlighted:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Colonial Undertones</strong> - Price Harry and Meghan told in the interview that they repeatedly got asked by any members of the royal family (whose name they wouldn’t disclose) about the complexion of their baby throughout pregnancy, asking “how dark” Archie’s skin might be?</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This racism contributed greatly to the reason why he and Meghan chose to part their ways from the royal family. Prince Harry told Oprah that he had no support from any of his relatives when the news and the articles related to Meghan and the “colonial undertones” got published.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Mental health: a Hush-Hush topic, still!</strong> - Meghan disclosed that at one point in time, it felt that life became so difficult that she “didn’t want to be alive anymore” and wanted to hurt herself. She said that she wanted to seek medical help and even asked for it, but was not granted aid- making her feel even more helpless in that household. People who’ve heard her remarks cannot seem to relate her story to Princess Diana’s, who also felt like an outsider and wanted to hurt herself due to the constant pressure from the royal hierarchy.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>The Most Pressing Question! </strong>Watching his wife surviving under constant pressure and not being able to help, Price Harry and Princess finally announced to step down from their royal duties in the March of 2020, and moving to California; this came as a shock to the whole family as they were not intimated about it beforehand.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Given the stepping down circumstances, we cannot stop to wonder about the most important question of all; as to how the Duke and Duchess of Sussex; Prince Harry and Meghan Markle are managing their personal finances after the news of Prince Harry getting cut-off financially by the royal family at the beginning of last year came out? Is their decision already proving to be the worst after all and manage finances on their own is as bad as it seems, or are they better off choosing any means of livelihood they want?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s elucidate the facts to gauge their current financial situation:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>Cash at hand</strong> - Town and Country estimated Meghan’s net worth at $5M in 2018. According to Forbes, Prince Harry inherited $13.3M from his late mother Diana when he turned 30. So, one thing is clear, they do have time to come up with a good enough financial strategy as they have a lot that could last them for a long while. Let’s talk about some of the options that are clearly in sight.</li><li>Meghan used to get $85,000 per episode of Suits, so making a comeback won’t be a bad option. As estimated by Forbes, these numbers will shoot-up. All thanks to the recent popularity she has gained.</li><li>They could choose to write a book and pen down their struggles in the Royal living as biographies from popular personalities are quite in demand in these. In 2017, the US former president Barak Obama and his wife Michelle Obama signed a $65M book deal, which makes it a very attractive means of livelihood</li><li>With the current support and sympathies they have gathered from the fans across the globe, they could start a podcast and engage with their audience as with 12M viewership for their 2-hour interview with Oprah, Harry and Meghan surely are the center of interest for people, hence they will not be short of the spectators.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Any official statement on what they do plan has not yet been released about how they are going to manage their finances, so let’s stay tuned and watch out for the news, for whatever they do is surely going to be something big!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Meghan and Harry’s interview & their most hinted Financial Strategies', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Don\'t Miss,Investment,Strategic Financial Management', NULL, NULL, '2021-06-05 09:14:12'),
(8, 'usdchf-expected-to-decline-further-a-great-opportunity-for-the-bulls', 'Tue, 16 Mar 2021 08:46:02 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>USDCHF has experienced a sharp decline during the last 3 days. The USDCHF pair fought hard to maintain its bullish trend that had been going on since last week but just as the European market came into action today, USDCHF lost the battle and slipped towards the depth that is now turning out to be a death warrant for the pair.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It all started in the Asian session when USDCHF tried hard not to come under the bear dominance. It kept a tight grip around the 0.9300 level but later during the European session it came crashing down to 0.9224 level. But the question here is:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Is USDCHF heading towards a consistent bearish trend? Or is it just a trap set by the bulls for a longterm gain?&nbsp;</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Well the answer is not that simple. Even though the current trend seems to go in favor of the bears, a strong bullish trend is expected very soon.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>An in-depth analysis&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While USD has been working hard to dominate its rivals once again, the natural market mechanisms have been going against it. US dollar index is being forced to play at the backfoot and the major reason behind this safe play is the falling T-bond yields. Wednesday proved to be chaos for the greenback as the treasury note auction took place which resulted in a sharp T-Bond drop.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a result, the US dollar index experienced a major decline of 0.5% and is currently down by 0.31% at 91.53 level. This development hurt the greenback and it lead to USD depreciation against major currencies. The current scenario shows how USDCHF is expected to drop even further but just looking at the US dollar index might not be a good idea.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To make things even more clear it is recommended to wait for the US labor report which give a further insight about the jobless claims that are being made. The results will predict the future journey of the USDCHF pair and the extent to which USD is expected to depreciate before rising again.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Important levels to watch</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>USDCHF pair is currently out on a risky journey. The pair might just be an illusion for the bears or it might actually turn out to be a crisis for the bulls. According to our research we have come up with some technical levels that would help you in decision making whether you\'re a small or a full time trader.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>1. USDCHF closing price: 0.9252</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>2. Change (%): -0.47</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>3. Previous daily high: 0.9323</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>4. Daily low: 0.9276</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>5. Monthly low: 0.8871</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The daily moving averages point toward a buying trend with a total of 11 moving average indicators predicting a buying trend against 1 sell indicator. Moreover, various other technical indicators have been pointing towards a strong buying trend, including: RSI (14), STOCH (9,6), CCI (14) etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Our Verdict&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the current trend is clearly in favor of the bears, our research goes in favor of the bulls. Right now the USDCHF pair is experiencing a sharp decline so if you\'re a scalper who\'s looking for a short term gain, go ahead and put on a sell order right away because USDCHF is expected to fall lower before jumping back to a new high record.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pair might touch the 0.88 level but that won\'t be an easy target as a strong support is expected when the market reopens on Monday.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep visiting our website for more forex news, signals, analysis, tips etc. Help us grow by sharing our website with your friends and family!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'USDCHF expected to decline further - a great opportunity for the Bulls', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Don\'t Miss,Investment,Stockwatch', '1623072095_markus-spiske-ms6N-gBtbCQ-unsplash (1).jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:21:35'),
(9, 'zoom-ceo-transfers-6-billion-worth-of-his-shares', 'Tue, 16 Mar 2021 08:51:51 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eric Yuan, founder of Zoom, sold 18 million shares of his company which were valued at around $6B by the regulatory filing. This decision came as a shock to investors and many have started questioning the future position of the online conferencing app.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eric Yuan is not just the founder but also the chief executive of his company so any decision that he makes causes a ripple effect that eventually reaches the investors. The 40% stake transfer by Yuan was shown as a \"gift to certain beneficiaries\" but till now their identity is kept hidden.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This has raised a doubt in minds of the investors and many are demanding details about the transfer. The move is being labeled as \"shady\" by some experts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":188,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/gabriel-benois-qnWPjzewewA-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-188\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A brief history</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yuan introduced the Zoom app back in 2011 and no one could\'ve possibly imagined how popular it would become 9 years later. In 2019, Yuan listed Zoom on the US stock market and quickly became a billionaire. His wealth skyrocketed when the global pandemic in the form of Covid19 started gaining strength in different parts of the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to Forbes, Yuan is currently worth 13.7 billion dollars. From a founder of an online application to becoming a part of the list of 100 most influential people, Yuan\'s journey has been a motivation for many.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Zoom gained global popularity during the pandemic, it caught the attention of millions of investors. With huge sums of money invested in Zoom, Yuan\'s transfer of 18 billion shares has now become a hot topic throughout the globe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why did Yuan decide to make this move?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The true intentions of Zoom founder are still a mystery but the media interviews have drawn a blurry picture which has helped us to identify possible reasons behind this transfer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The distributions were made in accordance with the terms of Eric Yuan and his wife\'s trusts\" a Zoom spokesperson revealed. As of now it is being portrayed that the huge transfer has something to do with Yuan\'s estate planning activities but to what extent this claim is legitimate is still a mystery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zoom profits tripled last year and the company currently values at around $100B. Gaining such strength in a short time period might have attracted attention of other players in the market.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Zoom founder Eric Yuan\'s decision to transfer more than a third of his stake will raise some eyebrows,\" said Edward Moya in an interview with BBC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What to expect</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As far as the stock market is concerned, Yuan\'s move might prove to be damaging for Zoom. A bearish trend is expected if Yuan doesn\'t reveal the identity of the receivers. A $6B gift is not what you see every other day so definitely this move will be welcomed by criticism and maybe some rumours as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Having said that, Zoom\'s executives made a different prediction during their annual meeting last week. Executives are expecting continued growth in 2021 and they feel confident about the company\'s future. Yuan explained in the following words:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The future is here with the rise of remote and work from anywhere change. We recognise this new reality\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zoom expects a sales growth of around 40% which would bring their revenues close to $4B leading towards appreciation of share prices as a result.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As of now, Zoom is the topic of the town and investors are feeling nervous about its future. Was the transfer pointing towards an acquisition? Is zoom about to be merged with a third party? Or was it actually a gift as they claim?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No one knows yet. Keep visiting our website to find out the answer. Don\'t forget to share and subscribe before leaving!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Zoom CEO transfers 6 billion worth of his shares', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Don\'t Miss,Investment,Stockwatch', '1623072060_gabriel-benois-qnWPjzewewA-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:21:00'),
(10, 'is-it-possible-to-get-away-with-tax-evasion-the-answer-is-no', 'Mon, 08 Mar 2021 14:46:12 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The process of tax return filing and payment is obligatory and you are bound by the laws of the US government to follow the legalities annually. However, if for some reason, you fail because you probably forgot to, or decide not to file your tax returns then the consequences you better get ready to face the consequences because the International Revenue Service keeps a close eye on your financial activities and you\'ll most definitely end up paying a heavy price for not filing in time or even so have your property seized by the IRS.  In the worst-case scenario, you may have to serve some jail time! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":163,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/kelly-sikkema-SiOW0btU0zk-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-163\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So what exactly happens if you&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>File your Income Tax Returns late, or maybe never file at all?</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the tax filing season starts every year, you have to pay an estimated tax amount to the IRS, which is</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Automatically deducted from your paycheck if you are a W-2 employee, or</li><li>Manual payment required from the taxpayer if you are a 1099 employee.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Failing to abide by the above clauses initiates a process of getting penalized with basic penalties by the state of law and local taxes offices. The fines keep on getting bigger with every passing month if you refrain from paying them in time. The IRS officials send a bill at your address along with a warning letter entailing a small penalty, i.e. a 0.5% interest of the pending tax returns; against every $1,000, you\'ll have to pay somewhere near $4. For each month thereafter, in case of non-payment till the said due date, an increment of 0.5% keeps getting added to the amount until the full tax has paid in full- or it reaches a 25% penalty threshold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you cross the final limit of not paying the tax, the IRS then has the legal right to claim the property and assets you own- referred to as \"lien\", after which confiscation of that property and assets occurs- referred to as \"levy\". Most of the time, the issue gets resolved at this stage, if not, then the culprit has to serve a <strong>five-year jail time</strong> for the crime of tax evasion (which won’t probably happen unless you owe the state thousands of dollars).&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you’ve completed the process of filing your tax return, you\'ll then be able to estimate the tax that has been paid was equal to, or more than the amount that needed to be paid. If found equal, will be considered as the tax bill, while any amount that has been paid in excess will be refunded to you or compensated in the next year’s tax payments. If you have been lucky for not yet been noticed by the IRS for the last 10 years, then you are in real fortune because the statute of limitations for the collection of late taxes is 10 years’ time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember, the due date for filing of the first quarter for the year 2021 is April 15<sup>th</sup>, 2021, so hurry up and get your record straight so as to save yourself from any predicaments in the future!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Is it possible to get away with Tax Evasion? The answer is NO!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Tax Returns', '1623072082_pexels-karolina-grabowska-5632379.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:21:22');
