(31, 'google-to-invest-7-billion-in-offices-thus-creating-10-000-jobs', 'Mon, 22 Mar 2021 17:11:57 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Google believes in providing flexibility to their workers and facilitating them with opportunities to work from home i.e. remotely or through offices. This is the definition of a “hybrid” model that Google wants to keep on exploring. Sundar Pichai; the CEO of Google said that “We firmly believe that in-person, being together, having a sense of community is super important when you have to solve hard problems and create something new so we don’t see that changing. But we do think we need to create more flexibility and more hybrid models.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is believed by Google that community-building is an important part of their culture and it is the most important way of building a future. Remote working will still be an option for those who opt for it, but, coming to offices and working from there is considered necessary for team building and other important aspects that may be crucial for getting certain tasks done which cannot be done from home. Pichai, while stating the means through while Google plans to boost the economy wrote; “I believe a lasting economic recovery will come from local communities, and the people and small businesses that give them life. Google plan to&nbsp;invest over $7 billion in offices and data centers across the U.S. and create at least 10,000 new full-time Google jobs in the U.S&nbsp;this year. This includes investing in communities that are new to Google and expanding in others across 19 states.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":239,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hk-Un-vHvg5ezU-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-239\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Enhanced Locations throughout the country:</strong><br>Google plans on expanding across the country and enhancing its presence across 19 states. Some major enhancements include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>A new data center in South Carolina</li><li>Another Cloud Engineering site in Durham &amp; North Carolina</li><li>Building an Operations center in Southaven, Mississippi.</li><li>New offices in Rochester, Minnesota, New Albany, Ohio, and Nebraska.<br></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to the pandemic, many people will be hesitant on returning to offices. Working remotely will be their preference although it does come with certain cons. Some of those might include being left out in meetings or not getting thoroughly communicated by other employees. Some of the people have even remarked that working from home has also started taking a toll on their mental health. According to a study, about “31% of couples admitted lockdown has caused irreparable damage to their relationships.” These stats make sense as juggling work and kids at the same time and at the same place is quite a task. Keeping all this and the expansion in view, Google is expecting workers to return to offices this fall and plans on allowing remote working for 2 days per week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The heads at Google Inc. are also planning on hiring members across diverse communities; this will help lower the racial discrimination that diverse communities get subjected to. According to Pichai, Google did more hiring of Black and Latinx in 2020 than was ever done in the previous years. Google was also one of the first companies that extended the time period of remote working and thus facilitated their employees. Google has committed $1 billion for affordable housing system and they also plan on doubling their workforce by 2028, which means that its income also keeps on increasing. It was reported that Gross sales for Google rose 46% from 2019 for its cloud unit.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Google to invest $7 billion In Offices, thus Creating 10,000 Jobs', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Don\'t Miss,Investment', '1623071208_pexels-miguel-a-padrinan-3785927.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:06:48'),
(32, 'baidu-s-homecoming-and-plans-for-partnership-for-ev', 'Mon, 29 Mar 2021 12:12:50 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Baidu- the renowned Chinese Search Engine made its debut in secondary listing in Hong Kong on Tuesday when it’d foreseen its shares rising at 0.8 percent above its opening list price of 255 HKD, equivalent to $32, thus allowing a raise of $3.1 billion. Robin Li- CEO of Baidu announced that all of these funds will be invested in emerging technologies which might include artificial intelligence-based OS, semi-conductor chips, or autonomous-driving platforms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":252,\"width\":593,\"height\":398,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/baidu-1024x688.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-252\" width=\"593\" height=\"398\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robin Li, in January, further proclaimed that they will be partnering with Chinese automaker Geely in order to achieve their goals of developing autonomous driving systems for their cars. The new company formed shall cater to the manufacturing of electric vehicles while incorporating the latest technology developed. Li said: “We are standing at a new starting line to realize our dream of changing the world with technology.” Li referred to it as homecoming, as their company’s headquarters are in Beijing and they operate mainly in the Chinese market, but he will be returning to Hong Kong’s capital market after years for the launch of this new tech. As excited as Li is about returning to the Chinese territory with the listing, Beijing is skeptical about Baidu and questions its ability as an innovator. According to Brock Silvers- Chief Investment Officer of Kaiyuan; \"Baidu’s open reflects the market’s lukewarm view for the company’s prospects. Baidu isn’t regarded as an effective technology innovator.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Anti-Trust push -</strong> Baidu was fined for SAMR $77000 by China’s market regulator for “Illegal monopolistic behavior”. China has always been looking for ways to limit the power and hence, the authority of the financial technology sector. It is against the monopolistic view that these companies might take. Li explained: \"You just cannot imagine the No. 1 and No. 2 guys suddenly merging and gaining more than 90% of market share in the U.S. But that has happened quite a few times in China before. That’s not good for innovation. So, I think that the antitrust push is justified,\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Baidu’s Popularity:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Baidu caters to a lot of China’s search engine market with around 544 million monthly users! With such a high user count, it can facilitate 69% of all internet searches in China. Li is therefore optimistic and says that these regulations may work for the benefit of Baidu and they may be able to convince China’s major tech players to become transparent with them and share their data with the search engine.</li><li>It was reported in November that the company experienced a 14% rise in “non-online marketing revenue”, which clearly signals that the generated profits were made from contributions in cloud computing and other artificial intelligence-based software.</li><li>Baidu has been experimenting with self-driving software for quite some time and is now able to harness data that will be helpful in training autonomous cars aiding in understanding and navigating through various road conditions. The market for EV is there in Hong Kong. Although investors are skeptical but will stand with the winning party. If Baidu can pull it off, they will surely vote in its favor.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Baidu’s Homecoming and Plans for Partnership for EV', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Don\'t Miss,Investment', '1623071186_pexels-miguel-a-padrinan-3785927.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:06:26'),
(33, 'notarize-raises-130-million-and-enjoys-600-growth', 'Mon, 29 Mar 2021 12:45:25 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Notarize is an electronic notary start-up whose founder and CEO Pat Kinsel was fielding 3000 calls a week last year and has since been successful in the acquisition of the attention of real estate brokers and financial advisors for being demanded to be set up on their service. Notarize has been very creative in selecting its clients and has spread across industries that included wealth management. This was all done when traction in the market like real estate climbed up by more than 800%. Kinsel exclaimed, “It was as though the entire world tried to digitize in a 10-day period”.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":255,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/money-2696235_640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-255\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What pushed Kisel? </strong>It was his experience that pushed him in the right direction as Kinsel is aware of the failed legal regulations when it comes to the digital world of the notary process. He got to know about it when he sold Spindle to Twitter in 2013. Spindle was his mobile data collection startup. This transaction caused a lot of hassle as there was a pile of documents that needed to be notarized. When the notary stamped but forgot to sign them, they all became invalid. This put off Kinsel but he was encouraged to correct this painstaking process as he spent years and tens of millions of dollars in order to navigate the notarization regulatory system. These requirements were different at federal, state, and even county levels. He had to travel to 40 states and was successful in passing 31 pieces of state legislation which paved the way for Notarize. His efforts proved to be fruitful in March 2020 when the world was shut down due to the Corona pandemic and the industries that operated on paper lagged because it depended on the connection between the physical world and the internet. According to the CEO “The reason we were doing well prior to Covid is because we had really created legal clarity in the market. Online is infinitely more convenient, but if it doesn’t have legal standing, it’s pointless.” The success was achieved as</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>It was successful in raising $213 million and saw growth of 600%. Kinsel boasted saying that “If we never sign another customer, but just process the volume, we are a $700 million revenue-business.”</li><li>Major companies such as Adobe, Zillow, and Transamerica were brought onboard</li><li>Financial services climbed up by 324%, auto insurance by 219%, and real estate by 835%.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, in order to accommodate the growing demand, Notarize has announced a $130 million round with a post-valuation of $760 million, led by Canapi Ventures, CapitalG, and TrueBridge Capital Partners along with some banks (such as Citi and Wells Fargo).&nbsp; They are also planning on adding the healthcare industry to their services, and the new capital acquired will be used by Notarize to expand its team.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Pat explained his expansion plans</strong> saying that “We are very focused on making these things possible. We want to be first and move these markets forward. There is still so much regulatory momentum, new industries being clarified or large commercial organizations moving into space for the first time. Our growth is continuing month over month.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Notarize raises $130 million and enjoys  600% Growth', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business', '1623071194_notary-public-stamp-1060x630-1.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:06:34'),
(34, 'eurusd-stuck-at-1-18-level-what-to-expect', 'Mon, 29 Mar 2021 12:49:06 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greenback has made a strong comeback and is ready to set a new high record very soon. As USD is stabilising, EURO is stuck in its bearish shell. The EURUSD pair has been wrestling around the 1.18 mark since the last few days and the match is now turning into a boring fight with no outcome.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interestingly, greenback kept on moving higher and has successfully entered the new high region of 2021. A major reason behind this push is the recent GDP report that has claimed a 4.3% gain overtaking the QoQ by a small yet effective margin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":261,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/lena-balk-Ki5pRv_OrS4-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-261\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So where exactly is USD headed and how will it impact the EURUSD pair in the coming weeks?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A brief Analysis</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The EURUSD pair saw a decline below the 1.18 level after 4 months of bullish influence. While the bears have had a fair share during the last 4 months, it was the bulls who had control of this pair. Right now EURUSD is facing an immense pressure from the bears and the current economic scenario in Europe predicts a further downfall in the coming months.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Covid19 has taken a boost throughout the globe and the 3rd wave is deadlier than ever. While Europe is fighting hard to defeat the culprit, the trend lines show a pessimistic future ahead. The third pandemic wave makes a strict lock down inevitable and with an investor point of view this might attract strict restrictions from the government as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If that\'s the case, Europe will experience another economic decline, pulling the EURUSD pair even lower into the bearish trap.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A statistical point of view</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the pandemic predictions show a pessimistic future for EURUSD, the statistical view shows a dead pitch with no real effects. Earlier today, the German Consumer Confidence improved to -6.2 for the upcoming month and that is not it, the Business confidence in France maintained its position at 98 this month. Furthermore, the private sector loans increased by 3% and the money supply has expanded by a moderate level of 13.3% but on the other hand, the US GDP improved the US economy by 4.30%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While some economic changes have occurred today in Europe and USA, the net effects of these economic changes have equalled to almost nothing and just like that the EURUSD pair continues to fight at the 1.18 level as today\'s session comes to an end.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Important EURUSD levels to note</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Currently the EURUSD index has depreciated by 0.13% and is expected to fall further before making a rebound again. The pair is being traded at 1.1796 right now and a weak support level is expected around the 1.1790 mark. The trend analysis predicts an easy defeat for this support level and the EURUSD is then expected to dive further down towards the 1.1750 mark but it will face a strong support by the bulls around the 1.1760 mark. If a corrective action doesn\'t appear soon, the pair might go below 1.1730 but having said that a strong support at the current position can push it towards the 1.20 level but chances of this happening are very thin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ll just have to wait and see where this pair turns next week. For more interesting content, don\'t forget to bookmark our website. Help us grow by sharing our content with your friends and family!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'EURUSD stuck at 1.18 level - what to expect?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currencies,Currency Market', '1623071150_europe-69526.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:05:50'),
(35, 'eurgbp-testing-0-8500-support-level-a-bearish-outlook', 'Mon, 29 Mar 2021 12:51:52 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The EURGBP pair is back under the influence of the bears and is right now testing the 0.8500s levels. This movement towards the bear cave was expected at the beginning of this month. While the pair is fighting hard to bounce back towards the north, it is currently being hammered down towards the south!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EURGBP saw a slight improvement 2 days ago around 0.8540 level but the net result continued to travel under shadows of the negative bias. Certain economic developments have been noticed in the Eurozone and UK that influenced the pair greatly and right now there\'s only one question in the minds of investors:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Is EURGBP moving towards the bearish trap or will the bulls take control of it?</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While this question has been ringing alarms throughout the week, Europe and UK has decided to cooperate with each other to take care of the economic challenges arising due to the third pandemic wave.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":264,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/pound-414418_640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-264\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The bigger picture</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EURGBP has started pushing upwards and is ready to break the resistance levels but the bearish grip is strong enough to hold it back. As of now, EURGBP is trading with a net loss of 0.1% which is roughly equal to 10 pips. This has been the scenario since the past few weeks and it is expected to continue in the next few weeks as well. The EURGBP has been trading between 0.8540 and 0.8640 range since the last 3 weeks which shows the kind of pressure it is in right now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The strong resistance levels at 0.8640 and the weaker support levels at 0.8540 are pointing towards a bearish trend next week. If the support level breaks at 0.8540, EURGBP is expected to crash towards 0.8000 level but that won\'t turn into a reality as the UK government and Europe has started taking steps to recover from heavy losses. Having said that, EURGBP might touch 0.8300 level before bouncing back above 0.8500 in which case the bulls will suffer heavy losses and some of them might even quit the game!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Future Predictions</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pair has been traveling on rough roads since the last few weeks but economic developments within Europe and UK might change the ending of this stressful story.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"The unexpectedly strong Ifo Business Climate Index (BCI) for March provides further evidence that, other than in the auto sector, Germany’s manufacturers are flourishing\"&nbsp;</em>a statement released by Capital Economics draws a clearer picture of the situation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the optimistic claim was opposed by an added pessimistic statement:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"The rest of the economy is faring less well, and the extension of the virus restrictions means a sustained recovery is unlikely until the second half of the year\"</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though most of the activities predict a positive outcome, the third wave of Coronavirus will prove to be damaging for the economy. Hence, the pressure of EURGBP continues to maintain its position.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Europe is drowning under deep water, UK on the other hand is moving towards a brighter future. The vaccine rollout has been successful in the mighty Kingdom and luckily, the hospitalization and death rates have reduced giving an edge to UK over the fellow G10 peers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With improving UK economy and increasing problems for Europe, the EURPGBP pair is expected to test the 0.8250 level by the mid of April. It is time to sell!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more helpful articles, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to share it with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'EURGBP testing 0.8500 support level - A bearish outlook?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currencies,Currency Market', '1623071133_pound-414418_640.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:05:33'),
(36, 'gold-is-set-to-recover-approaching-1800s-level-again', 'Tue, 06 Apr 2021 10:48:17 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The king of metals has finally decided to return from its bearish journey that started a few weeks ago. The yellow metal has now bounced back from its multi-month lows and has begun its bullish journey today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The negative streak finally ended during the opening trading hours today and XAUUSD jumped above the 1700 level near $1710. The next resistance point is expected to occur somewhere near $1720 but XAUUSD seems to be strong enough to break it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":270,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/pexels-michael-steinberg-321452.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-270\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Where is XAU headed?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Monday and Tuesday haven\'t been very lucky for the yellow metal. For two consecutive days, Gold and Silver both have been facing heavy losses were deep under control of the bears. While this has been the case at the beginning of the week, certain economic developments in the US have helped Gold and Silver to make a rebound and claim back the higher positions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The yields saw a decline in USA this week and the dollar successfully bounced back towards the north to some extent and the financial returns were slightly better which helped the greenback rise up again. With USD appreciating against major currencies, it became an invisible hand in case of Gold and pushed it higher as well. The ripple effect of this movement has caused the prices of silver to increase as a result.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Previously, XAUUSD was pushed off the bullish mountain by the bears and it ended up near $1675 where the bulls fought back again. The strong support level at $1675 helped gold to make a comeback in the market and it crossed $1700, reaching near $1710 point today. All this happened during the Asian session and the investors in USA are going to be surprised tomorrow!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Why is XAUUSD moving up?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some see this as a result of economic improvement in USA while others completely disagree. We have conducted an in-depth analysis which has helped us reach a conclusion. The upward movement of gold is not as simple as it seems to be and might turn in any direction in the coming weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the bearish pullback, XAUUSD fell below 1700s level. As it moved towards 1680 level, indicators starting ringing an oversold alarm. XAUUSD kept on declining further and a strong bounce back was then expected. So the movement that we see now is to some extent a result of a corrective action that is still taking place as you read this article. The rule is simple, anything that gets overbought or oversold is bound to move in the opposite direction. This, exactly happened with gold when it touched the $1675 support level this week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the upper movement of XAUUSD is not just limited to this phenomenon. Another major reason behind the rebound is the US yields. Gold is directly linked to the US yields and any movement in the yield would make a direct impact on gold itself. However, it is interesting to note that on Wednesday the XAUUSD pair moved upwards despite a retreat taking place in the US treasury yields. This might be because of the corrective action we discussed above and also due to the dollar appreciation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Final Words</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While XAUUSD\'s upward movement seems temporary, the indicators and our analysis believe it is set to make reach a new high of 2021. USD is currently under pressure and the yields are moving rapidly every day. However, XAU seems to have made a decision that says:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Keep&nbsp; moving upwards till the bears cry\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Having said that, this is the right time to buy XAUUSD because a strong bullish trend is expected to continue during the next 5 trading days.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more helpful articles, keep visiting our website!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Gold is set to recover - Approaching 1800s level again?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Don\'t Miss,Gold,Investment', '1623071119_pexels-michael-steinberg-342942.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:05:19'),
(37, 'eurusd-continues-to-recover-above-1-1750-usd-under-pressure', 'Tue, 06 Apr 2021 10:50:41 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greenback has been fighting for an upward position since the last few weeks now. Joe Biden\'s $1.9 trillion dollar helped the US economy to recover from the damages caused by Covid19 to some extent but greenback continues to face increased pressure due to other economic issues that have risen during the last 2 weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The struggle to achieve a higher position in the market has, in fact, pushed greenback downwards and as a result the currency has been depreciating against all major currencies. USD lost against AUD, GBP, EUR and CAD during this bearish journey and it is interesting to note that the weaker currencies are now also gaining strength against the mighty dollar. For example, USDPKR which was once 168 has recovered strongly and is currently being traded around 152 levels. This shows the kind of trouble being faced by dollar right now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The EURUSD had been influenced by the bears previously but as greenback started losing, a recovery was noticed and currently the pair has successfully crossed 1.1750 level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":273,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/pexels-dom-j-45110.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-273\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Are bulls taking control of EURUSD?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The DXY which had started improving slightly at the beginning of the week has now turned 180° and is falling back towards the south. The lower yields in USA today pushed DXY below 93.00 mark, increasing the already expanding losses by a big margin. On the other hand, EURUSD continued its bullish journey that began two days ago. The question here is, how long will the bulls dominate?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As USA revealed financial and economic data, EURUSD saw this as an opportunity to gain back what it lost earlier. The pair first jumped back to 1.1735 level which was seen as a quick recovery and it broke the moderate resistance levels to continue traveling upwards. As the week came to an end, EURUSD reached its new weekly highs on Thursday when it touched the 1.1775 level. This is the highest position of EURUSD since the Asian session that was held on last Tuesday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bullish formation helped Euro to gain confidence of investors and as a result the overall outlook of EURUSD pair turned bullish, breaking any resistance that came in the way. A major reason behind a sudden upwards move was the weakening US dollar. The opposite movement of the two rivals caused the pair to rise back up above the previous week\'s high.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, ISM came to support the pair just when it needed the most. The latest ISM readings were revealed to be better than what was expected and these readings added a further positive touch to the pair\'s journey on Thursday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>DOW Jones gained 0.48%, slightly above its previous day\'s closing limit while NASDAQ performed well enough to gain 1.55% helping the overall economic indicators to appreciate. On the other hand, US treasury yields bounced off the cliff and went crashing down by a margin of 1.67% along with DXY which went below 93.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What to expect?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sudden upward movement has broken the immense bearish pressure that had been kicking the pair downwards consistently over the past few days. The pair, however, still has a long term bearish outlook in comparison to its short-term bullish trend. The Euro has seen slight improvement and is expected to move up before the greenback would take control of it again. If that\'s the case, EURUSD is expected to cross 1.1850 level in the short-term before the bears will pull it back near 1.1700 level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a great opportunity to buy the pair if you\'re a short-term investor and sell the pair if you\'re looking to follow a longterm strategy. For more helpful information, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to subscribe before leaving!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'EURUSD continues to recover above 1.1750 - USD under pressure', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currencies,Currency Market,Don\'t Miss,Investment', '1623071105_british-1209730.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:05:05'),
(38, 'live-streaming-is-the-talk-of-today', 'Tue, 06 Apr 2021 10:58:39 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the recent upsurge in the use of social media platforms, the trend of communicating to the public through live stream on the internet has increased drastically. 2021 is expected to be the booming year for businesses targeting the market through audio and video streaming. According to Neal Schaffer- a social media consultant; “If your business wants to survive in organic social media in 2021, I believe that this sort of humanization of your brand will be necessary.” China has been strategizing the use of online shopping to boost its economy in sales of $61 billion in the year 2019 to a high of $129 billion in 2020.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":279,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/paul-mcgrath-YjWU8G4J9xI-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-279\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What is Live Streaming and how widely is it used?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This term refers to the use of audio and video for real-time broadcasting of activities over the internet to the viewers.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Live streaming has become extensively popular in the professional world and the trend is so widely adopted and practiced by almost all of the topnotch businesses and organizations to connect to their audience and engage the maximum amount of users and establish a deeper bond despite physical barriers;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Google</strong> <strong>Inc.</strong> announced Shoploop</li><li><strong>Instagram Inc.</strong> launched Reels and IGTV in 2021.</li><li><strong>Tiktok</strong>- Live Streaming champion for 2020</li><li>November 2020: Official launch of Women’s fashion brand ANNE KLEIN in-app shopping on Facebook live in&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Shopify</strong> partners with TikTok</li><li><strong>Youtube</strong> is also “testing a new beta program with a group of beauty and electronics creators to help people discover and buy the products they see in videos,” says Susan Wojcicki</li><li><strong>LinkedIn video</strong></li><li><strong>Tweet streaming:&nbsp;</strong>A&nbsp;new&nbsp;live-streaming feature on Twitter.</li><li><strong>Facebook Watch</strong> by Facebook Inc.</li><li>Other key players in the live streaming market include Amazon.com, Empire Video, Productions LLC, Flux Broadcast, IBM Corporation, Periscope, Twitch Interactive Inc., Microsoft Corporation, Vimeo, etc.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Benefits of Live streaming:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greatest use of Live streaming which directly affects the market is the connection it establishes between the merchant and his target audience. It is a 2-way street, where not only the merchant benefits through the live video streaming monetization along with the proliferation in his online sales and marketing with cost-effective solutions, but the viewer also stays updated with the latest trends and gets easy access to his desired item. Additionally, both parties get to communicate at their ease and convenience with a variety of content, allowing maximum possible customer support, privacy, and security. However, with such like demand, the value of video quality and video analytics for better services is a given!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Market growth Trends:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Live Streaming Market:</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By 2027; expected to touch $247.27 Billion, with a CAGR of 28.1%</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Video Streaming Software Market:</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The expected growth is from $6.1 billion in the year 2020 to $15 billion by 2025, with a CAGR of 19.7%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Another important element is the expansion of <strong>videoconferencing tools and platforms</strong> for remote working like Zoom, Cisco\'s Webex, Google Hangouts, GoToMeeting, BlueJeans by Verizon, etc.</li><li>Emerging startups venturing out to facilitate remote working include Tandem, Eloops, Figma, Slab, and Bluescape, etc.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Live Streaming is the talk of today', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Economics', '1623071092_pexels-joseph-redfield-2883051.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:04:52'),
(39, 'reshaping-the-future-with-chatbots-and-virtual-assistants', 'Mon, 12 Apr 2021 13:08:59 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most innovative and emerging technologies in today’s era is the Chatbot technology, mostly adopted for eLearning and deployed as virtual assistants.&nbsp;It has greatly helped in bridging the gap between education and technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What is a Chatbot? </strong>These are artificial intelligence (AI) backed computer programs that depend on machine learning and work through understanding the input language; spoken or written, and responding to it through simple keywords about specific subjects. These computer programs mock human behavior by generating text through using Natural Language Processing (NLP), making chatbots revolutionary. The chatbots work on the results formed by constant analysis of human text, speech, and facial expressions to generate tailored characteristics for enhanced customer support.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":292,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/ali-abdul-rahman-TS5Pi8jqJZY-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-292\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Market Scope and trends</strong>: This state-of-the-art technology has extensive applications in several industries; be it healthcare, real estate, or technological market for the cost-reduction, enrichment of quality, and collection of real-time data through continuous machine learning. The companies are integrating chatbot agents to minimize the workload on the human workforce by implementing it into mobile applications to provide help and support to the target audience when needed. In the near future, chatbots are expected to extend their horizon to integrate conversations based on real-time advanced predictive analytics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the year 2018, the worth of the chatbot market according to The Research and Markets was $1.2 billion, $17.17 billion in 2020, is<strong> anticipated to reach $7.5 billion by the year 2024</strong> and $102.29 billion by 2026 with a CAGR value of 34.75%, owing to the increasing demand of AI-based real-time technologies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>69% of consumers use chatbots to efficiently communicate with a brand, according to Salesforce.</li><li>Google Inc. launched <strong>Meena</strong> in 2020 based on data mining, with 2.6 billion parameters in the AI chatbot</li><li>Chatbots are extensively being used in the <strong>healthcare sector</strong>, e.g. Premera Blue Cross launched Premera Scout, Northwell Health integrated chatbots for its oncology patients, Mayo Clinic adapting to voice-activated chatbots, etc.</li><li>Due to Covid-19, the application of chatbots has increased tremendously due to the remote working conditions, in order to relieve the burden on the employees. E.g. <strong>WHO launched a WHO Health Alert</strong> system to offers instant information regarding the pandemic via Facebook Messenger</li><li><strong>Voice bots</strong> are becoming mainstream, envision 50% of all searches by 2021 to be driven by voice commands, according to Forbes.</li><li><strong>Online payments </strong>through Chatbots, like MasterCard’s chatbot for customer payments.</li><li>The <strong>key players</strong> in the market adopting chatbot technology include Dialogflow by Google Inc., IBM Corporation, Amazon Lex by Amazon Web Services Inc., etc.</li><li>In the <strong>banking industry</strong>, Floatbot is a chatbot integrated by Andhra Bank that can support a load of up to 50 million customers.</li><li>Almost 67% of US millennials told Chatbots Magazine that they would prefer purchasing products and services from different brands by using chatbots.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With such advancements on regular basis, it is justified to say that the chatbot industry will grow into being the driving force of various business segments, making use of NLP for sentiment and predictive analytics to interact with humans more effectively and efficiently, guaranteeing a pleasant customer experience. Other predicted uses for chatbots are shown:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":291,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/xs.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-291\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Source: Digital Marketing Community</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Reshaping the Future with Chatbots and Virtual Assistants', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business', '1623071080_pexels-polina-zimmerman-3747075.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:04:40'),
(40, 'new-highs-for-palladium-and-a-bearish-trap-for-gold-what-to-expect', 'Mon, 12 Apr 2021 13:15:00 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The king of metals, Gold, has been experiencing a downward pressure since the past few days and the bears are ready to trap it in their caves. 2021 hasn\'t been a lucky year for Gold, it has seen the top and the bottom of the mountain and the journey continues to grow difficult with the passage of time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From 1800s levels to a bearish pull down at 1600s level, Gold has experienced volatility like never before. A huge $1000 decline in XAU earlier this year made many bulls bankrupt. Heavy losses in Gold occurred which turned into a party for the bears but a nightmare for bulls.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since then, Gold has been unstable and just as it was approaching towards a potential bullish trend, certain economic developments combined with a change in rival metals price mechanisms has once again pushed Gold under the bearish influence and the future outlook doesn\'t seem very bullish at all!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":295,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/pexels-michael-steinberg-366551.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-295\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>XAU vs Palladium - Analysis</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The third wave of Covid19 has changed the trading trends, expectedly. As the second wave was coming to an end, major economies began their bounce back process and were set to rise again but unfortunately the third pandemic wave has brought everything to a halt, yet again. As a result, currencies like USD, JPY, GBP, EUR etc faced huge declines and aimed towards the bottom as the economies in the respected countries deteriorated.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now as we move towards the mid of 2021, the third wave of coronavirus is expected to get weaker which would cause the economic down trends to turn 180 degrees but that won\'t happen until the next few months.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the vaccination rollout and its success in many countries has given a green signal to the Capital Economics Strategists who have drawn a conclusion that if the vaccination rollout continues at this rate, economies are expected to reopen and re-operate at full capacity later this year. The bigger picture shows a normal 2022, the base of which would be laid during the ending months of this year.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If things go as planned, an improvement in economies would bolster the risky assets and as a result the pressure would be shifted to Gold which is the last thing an investor would want at this stage. What\'s more alarming is that the recent developments have pushed the prices of Palladium higher than Platinum prices and this bulish trend is expected to last a few years!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In such a scenario, Gold is likely to depreciate, especially when some investors are planning to replace the yellow metal with Bitcoin. It seems like right now, attacks are being made on Gold from all sides and the poor metal will have to fight hard in order to claim higher positions.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Our verdict&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The price of Palladium have risen by a huge 14% in March and it is expected to beat Platinum in the upcoming years as well. On the other hand, Gold that had stayed steady for a short period of time is once again under pressure and much of the blame can be given to the US treasury yields that have been rising and falling since the last few weeks. The long dated real yields in USA are expected to see a continued growth in which case all weights would be transfered at Gold, in short, the yellow metal is in deep trouble.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The King is falling and the bears are enjoying it. Right now is the time to join the Bears and sell Gold before its too late. The price levels are expected to fall further before rising up again. A strong bullish trend can be expected by the end of next month but the April is definitely the montb of bears so don\'t get fooled by minor upward trends as they are nothing but a trap being set by the bears.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep visiting our website for more interesting content. Don\'t forget to share this article with your friends and family, help us grow!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'New highs for Palladium and a bearish trap for Gold - What to expect?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Gold', '1623071044_pexels-michael-steinberg-366551.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:04:04');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `post_url`, `pubDate`, `post_date`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `post_author`, `post_category`, `post_image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(41, 'wall-street-stock-market-opens-mixed', 'Mon, 12 Apr 2021 13:19:11 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the title says, the stocks market in the US opened mixed on this Thursday. This occurred when there was another, to be precise the second time there was an increase in the weekly claims regarding jobless or unemployment benefits which was playing a part as a reminder that the progress of the economy is not smooth or balanced due to the lockdown.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Furthermore, there a decrease in the points for Dow Jones, its industrial average fell to 15 points, maybe even less than 0.1%, at around 33,432 points (9:35 AM ET). However, it was seen that there was an upward trend for S&amp;P 500 by 0.3%. Nasdaq composite was also at a rise by 0.9% while the news of Wednesday was being accepted by market regarding the tax plans laid by Biden administration which would target less number of businesses/ companies as compared to the initial expected number.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before all this happened, the prior jobless claims had risen up to 744,000 according to the reports by Labor Department - last week. Hopes were disappointing because of the falling trend. Although, prediction by the economists was estimated to 680,000.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The yields were further effected by the data, l 10- Year treasury bonds were at a fall by 1.64%. During the past week the points further lowered down to 11 basis points. Bank shares like Citigroup, JPMorgan and Bank of America, all these 3 faced a loss of 1% or greater in the initial trading which was lead by the recent pressure and focus on their lending margins.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>In addition, the stock for the Constellation Brands dropped down to 4.6% post the issuance of guidance</strong> by the company for the year. The fourthly fiscal quarter showed a drastic impact on the operating margins, especially as a result of the negative effect on the wines division which was caused by the wildfires.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Similarly, After ConAgra Foods said that it is anticipating a compression in the operating margins it has a stock opened at 2.2%. The compression was referred to the next 3 months period and not because of the rising input expenses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stock for Beyond Meat (Nasdaq) had an upward trend of 2.3% following the announcement of a deal which was about expanding and widening its distribution along the main and important grocery chains. These grocery chains include Target, Wegmans and Kroger.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going further, there were strains and restrictions faced by the automotive industry because of the global decrease in supply of semiconductors, and the evidence of this was noted. General Motors also had a warning run that it maybe a temporary situation that would idle more of the plans in North America because of the shortages. A statement by Volkswagen referred that it couldn’t possibly rule out the \"adjustment\" which further effected the production volumes for the year. In the most recent weeks there is a high raise in the General Motors stock ever since they have come out of their bankruptcy which happened as a consequence of the great recession, 2.4% fall. The Volkswagen ADRs dropped down to 0.8%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Wall Street - Stock Market Opens Mixed', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Don\'t Miss,Investment', '1623071027_lloyd-blunk-vrSKrUEZsDY-unsplash-1.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:03:47'),
(42, 'usdcad-reaches-new-daily-lows-as-canada-reveals-a-strong-jobs-report', 'Mon, 12 Apr 2021 13:30:09 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greenback has been losing against all major currencies since the past week and now the Canadian dollar has found an edge against it but this time the reason is not the weakening US economy, in fact, it is the strengthening Canadian economy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The remarks by Fed chairman Powell and the improving economic conditions in Canada has provided a strong bearish base to the USDCAD pair. The pair has ended in red color for 2 consecutive days now and a similar pattern is expected tomorrow as well. The strong support levels set by the bulls seem to be weakening and a resistance has been noticed on points which should\'ve been a support.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Right now bears are in control of the trends and the bulls can\'t do much about it. Let\'s have a look at some economic developments that changed the trends in a short time period.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":305,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/michelle-spollen-P22AFmgMuUc-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-305\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why is USDCAD falling?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a recent meeting, Canada revealed its latest jobs report which became a major reason behind the trend shift. Despite the dollar index experiencing tiny gains around 92.20 level, the decrease Canadian unemployment percentage won the race. It was reported that the unemployment rates in Canada declined to 7.5% in March which was a little more than the predicted percentage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This revelation boosted the investor confidence in the Canadian economy and analysts straight away predicted a strong CAD against USD which led to a bearish trend in USDCAD pair. However, initially the trend came under a bullish trend when it reached 1.2600 level earlier today. The pair followed a defense mechanism and reversed back to the 1.25s levels as the day passed by and ended at 1.2535 which is a net daily loss of around 0.22%. All thanks to Statistics Canada\'s unemployment report.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is interesting to note that the predicted unemployment percentage was 8%-8.2%, however, the actual percentage of 7.5% was surprisingly lower and came as a shock to the bulls. Furthermore, the same report revealed that the employment had increased by a huge number, 300000, during the same time period.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to improving Canadian stats, the declining US stats became a major reason behind the bearish USDCAD. The 10 year treasury yield lost traction and gained more than 4% on Friday morning, as a result DXY fell lower than the opening levels bringing USD within reach of the bearish claws. It is however important to note that DXY ended with a slight gain by the end of the day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, the US Bureau of Labor Statistics revealed its report as well. The results were positive but the outcome was nearly equal to zero. The PPI showed an increase to 3.1% which was slightly higher than the predicted 2.7% but unfortunately, it failed to receive a strong market reaction. Hence, the results made no real impact on USDCAD on Friday. It is interesting to note that WTI is also continuing to decline below $60 but as of now it is making no impact on CAD and the pair continues to fall under the bearish influence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is a great opportunity for the bears to short at this moment because a rebound is not expected soon. For more informational content, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to share it with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'USDCAD reaches new daily lows as Canada reveals a strong jobs report', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currencies,Currency Market,Economics', '1623071014_annie-spratt-JFJqno28onk-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:03:34'),
(43, 'dovish-powell-commentary-pushes-eurusd-above-1-19', 'Mon, 12 Apr 2021 13:25:21 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The much awaited bullish trend is back in action, EURUSD has finally managed to end its bearish streak after Dovish Powell commentary was released worldwide. Federal chair Powell gave his remarks today which pushed EURUSD higher than expected. While bears were looking at a favourable trend, it was the bulls who got away with the victory.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":301,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://summitstocks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/pexels-karolina-grabowska-4386158.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-301\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the question is, what exactly did Powell say? And why it made a negative impact on the greenback?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His remarks were quite simple but close to reality. Powell argued that USA was in trouble as the vaccination process throughout the country has slowed down and covid19 patients have been increasing with every passing day. It is important to note that scientists throughout the globe are trying hard to find a danger free way that can end the virus quickly but till now many have failed. In fact, the second wave of covid, which was once predicted to be the last wave turned out to be a beginning point for the third wave. The third wave is more deadlier and is spreading rapidly throughout the globe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new predictions are pointing towards and extended journey of covid19 that can continue till 2023-2024. The given circumstances has damaged the financial markets throughout the globe and as Powell accepted the facts, EURUSD climbed higher towards the bullish peak.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A brief summary</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pair is currently trading around the 1.19 level after it took back its lost position around 1.1883 which was a moving average point for the last 200 days. Today\'s sessions revealed a convincing performance after which the bulls would be looking forward towards setting up new high record around 1.1974-2.00 range. If that happens, EURUSD will go a long way up and maybe touch 2.25 as a result of the bullish push but that would just be a case of overbought function which would soon face a corrective mechanism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our analysis highlights the main reasons why EURUSD is now under influence of the bulls and it is interesting to note hiw EUR is just a silent partner in the given scenario. It was the greenback that became the cause of push in EURUSD as it deteriorated after announcement of Powell which led to low confidence of investors in the Economy of USA. Powell highlighted the future unemployment which is expected to increase in USA, currently the rate stands at 20% which is damaging for the economy and might even cause trouble for the Government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, despite Biden\'s actions to improve the economic outlook of the country, Powell argued that inflation had been a major issue during the pandemic and it is expected to rise with the passage of time. The year after year inflation is deeply embedded in the economy as of now and it might turn out to be the biggest problem for USA during the next 3 years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EURUSD is currently trading in favor of the bulls and the trend seems to be continuing during the next 2 weeks as well. Right now is the time to buy EURUSD pair and the bears need to rethink about their current strategies as heavy investments in the pair right now could lead to heavy losses!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more informational content, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to share it with your friends and family!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Dovish Powell Commentary Pushes EURUSD above 1.19', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currencies,Currency Market,Don\'t Miss,Investment', '1623071005_annie-spratt-JFJqno28onk-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:03:25'),
(44, 'german-s-fiscal-policy-barter-in-2021', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 14:39:43 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Germany is considered to be one of the emerging super powerful countries in the world. The country has established itself in all the aspects of life and emerging as a strong contender in leading the world’s economy. From the industrial level to the trade level, Germany has emerged as a leading economic giant. The biggest companies like Mercedes are perceived as the main contributors to the German economy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Vows to the new German government and fresh beginnings:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the start of 2018, after the general elections were held in the country, a collative government was formed in the country between the Conservatives and the Social Democrats. This government was known as the GroKo 111, and it was the third collaborative government. This government decided after the first 6 months that they should bring forward a change in the government’s fiscal policy, hence decided to invest in education and infrastructure. The total expected boost in the economy was about EUR 79.6 billion, which was 2.4% of the annual GDP in 2018-2021 as per the plan. These 2 sectors were a rapid stimulation for a major contribution in the GDP- given all the other factors are excluded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Contributors in Fiscal policy</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By increasing the investment in the education sector through the foundation of multiple educational institutions, opportunities for the investors as well as the students can raise the bar in GDP. Public investments in these fields can lead to a boost in the growth rate of the economy from 0.2% to 0.5% per year. This is considered as one of the finest rates which can change the driving force in a country’s progression. The progression of any country depends on the investment that is brought into the country. Germany gets the advantage in this perspective by having fair trading relations and investing relations with other countries. Various German companies offer investing opportunities globally to various tenders; e.g. for startup companies, they offer EUR 1 Million to multi-billionaire level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Prediction Regarding Fiscal Policy</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Globally economists are quite hopeful and positive about this new change in the policy. This can be a game-changer in the global economic forum as well as world politics. The Annual GDP at the time is 1.4%, which can be increased to 1%.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to statistics, the fiscal multiplier can be increased up to 0.77% of the total GDP. These policies can be a small change for now as the GDP is 1% but in the coming years, when the investments will increase, the GDP will automatically start snowballing and can be brought up to the mark up of 5% within 5 years. Hence, a 5-year economic plan can be a useful resource for the country as it can be a guide for the upcoming plans that will open up broader aspects for increasing the growth rate and revenue of the country.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'German’s Fiscal Policy Barter in 2021', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,Hot Updates,Investment', '1623070984_mika-baumeister-Xpsjx1PNnvo-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:03:04'),
(45, 'over-550-spacs-file-to-go-public-on-us-exchange', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 14:42:33 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to Bloomberg, more than 550 blank cheque companies have filed to go public on US Exchange this year, seeking to raise more than 160 billion USD. Rich and famous personalities like Shaquille O’Neal, Colin Kaepernick, Peyton Manning are linked with Special Purpose Acquisition Companies, one of the hottest investment phenomena. Once SPACs officially goes public on US Exchange, they will raise more money than all of 2020 combined!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This investment trend returned to news when a Southeast Asian start-up, Grab Holdings, agreed to a SPAC merger, valuing it at a whopping 40 billion USD this Tuesday. With the said merger, this ride-hailing and food delivery app has become the biggest blank cheque deal on record.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What are SPACs?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SPACs are especially popular with entrepreneurs as they help set up their company much easily, avoiding red tape, the steep fees associated with an IPO, and looking to raise capital to get listed on the US Stock Exchange without hassles of getting involved in other technicalities. SPAC is a shell company that lists itself on Stock Exchange, raising investments. Then it takes that pool of cash to invest in a late-stage start-up. However, if SPAC fails to do so in two years, the shell company liquidates. This time crunch creates an urgency to invest, making it popular with entrepreneurs with bright ideas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What does this mean for Wall Street?</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, SPACs are looking to raise billions of dollars in the stock market, but is it really good news? This trend is being looked at with skepticism and doubts by Wall Street watchdogs, SEC. They’re advising investors to not invest money in these trending shell companies just because of celebrity endorsements. This statement was released, “not to make investment decisions related to SPACs based solely on celebrity involvement”. SEC further stated that “sponsors may have conflicts of interest so their economic interests in the SPAC may differ from shareholders. Investors should carefully consider these risks.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whereas Acting Director John Coates released a statement saying, “Any simple claim about reduced liability exposure for SPAC participants is overstated at best, and potentially seriously misleading at worst.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dupont Capital’s Arch pointed out the hockey-stick projection of SPACs; flat revenue for several years then a forecast to turn higher sharply. This is concerning for investors. This is backed by IPOX SPAC Index which tracked SPACs rise from 500 points on its launch date on July 31, 2020, to a peak of 940 on February 17 – a gain of 88 percent, according to Refinitiv data. It has since fallen by a little more than 21 percent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So why do SPACs seem to rise and fall with such margins? DuPont Capital’s Arch explains, “I think that what the market may have realized is that not every deal is going to go up, … There’s good IPOs, there’s bad IPOs, there’s going to be good back deals with great targets and a good match between the management sponsor the back, and there’s going to be ones that are viewed less favorably.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Over 550 SPACs file to go public on US Exchange', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates,Stockwatch', '1623070977_michael-fortsch-SIz6izQKxzs-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 08:02:57'),
(46, 'alibaba-punished-by-china-for-an-anti-monopoly-case', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 14:44:40 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>China has given a major hit to the giant retailer of the country with a heavy penalty. The investigation started in the month of December 2020 and resulted in some proofs to be found against Alibaba, as reported by The New York Times. The net worth of the fine imposed by the government on Alibaba is about $2.8 billion which is equivalent to 18.2 billion Yuan, making this amount to be - by far- the most expensive fine ever imposed by the Chinese government on any company. The last time such a heavy penalty got imposed was in the year 2015 on a US-based company Qualcomm.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Reason for penalty:</strong> The giant retailer was found manipulating the rules and regulations passed by the Chinese Government. The platform was not giving any opportunity to the sellers to use any other platform, other than their own, for the buying and selling of their products. The investigation that commenced in the month of December found out that Alibaba was using algorithms that utilized user’s data to strengthen their place in the market, which was proving detrimental to the new sellers. The market found out the negative effect of this strategy regulating in the country within no time which was forming grounds for new chaos. The main purpose of this investigation was to find out that if the techno giant has been abiding by the rules and regulations, or imposing sanctions on the retailers. Before this incident the net worth of Alibaba in 2020 was nearly $21,080 million which got affected up to 2 million dollars. The amazing aspect is that their worth of shares in the stock market remain unaffected.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The reaction of Alibaba</strong>: The government elaborated that choosing the policy of using only one platform is not justified to the sellers and this can give them loss and unfair advantages to rule the world of technology. Upon imposition of the fine by the government, the company had to accept their mistake and pay the fine, along with the submission of 4% of the company’s revenue of the year, making it the heaviest fine ever imposed on any company by the People’s Republic of China. In a statement issued by the company, they accepted their mistake and promised to abide by all the rules and regulations of the country in the future and avoid any such blunders that can cause an adverse effect on their reputation and finances. The company will also commence a conference in Hong Kong to discuss the details and further proceedings about the fine. An official statement was also released from the company in which they have said that it was due to competency of government that they have achieved the landmarks in the field of trade however they will keenly look into this matter and will fill the loopholes as well. It is also reported that because of the news of fine imposition, the rating and popularity of Jack Ma also affected, and his persona was dropped from the spotlight.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is also reported that China is going to start a major crackdown against the biggest conglomerates and tech-savvy companies. The regulators are highly concerned over the growth of the companies that play a significant role in the financial sector.&nbsp; According to the recent reports, the total fine imposed on Alibaba is equal to the quarter-year profit of the company. This setback, however, was an eye-opener for all other companies who were trying to break the rules and regulations.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Alibaba punished by China for an Anti-Monopoly case!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Hot Updates,news,News &amp; Updates,popular', '1623070545_markus-winkler-29luexl03H4-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:55:45'),
(47, 'cryptocurrencies-taking-huge-strides', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 14:46:23 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week’s Wednesday turned out to be a good day for cryptocurrency holders when Coinbase Global Inc. became the first major crypto-centered startup to list on the US exchange. Not much time has passed since bitcoins and digital currency were looked at as a nefarious investment that was said to be helping criminals- a vain form of currency, and a dubious exchange of money. When the first major crypto-centered startup began trading on a United States exchange, skeptics were hit with a surprise. However, cryptocurrency is extremely unpredictable as values witnessed to have plummeted as low as 80%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What does it mean for cryptosphere?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cryptosphere is an eco-system of digital currencies, assets, blockchain, and exchanges. Coinbase Global Inc. chose to go public through direct listing, where existing shareholders sold shares directly to the public. Trading under the ticker symbol COIN, the market was opened for trading on Nasdaq at $381 a share that quickly ascended as high as $429.54, before losing steam to close at $328.28, i.e. roughly 14 percent lower than its opening price.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One mustn’t forget that Bitcoin’s value has also accelerated remarkably since October last year when PayPal Holdings announced it would launch a service to let customers buy, hold and sell cryptocurrencies directly from their PayPal accounts. This service will be available to US customers for now. They also announced that they will launch a service where transactions to buy and sell could be made using cryptocurrency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One Bitcoin was worth around $29,000 at the start of January. On Wednesday it shattered through $64,000!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shares of cryptocurrency going public will be good news for buyers who are still reluctant to buy a token or a coin directly. They can now buy shares, like of any other company, and enjoy the highs and lows like they would of any other stocks! Coinbase Global Inc going public via direct listing has empowered cryptocurrency and has opened gates of a very futuristic digital economy.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not only individuals are bearing the fruit of this digital currency listing, but small and major companies have also started stockpiling Bitcoin, tallying it to their wallets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ongoing pandemic has also given a boost to this trend as investors see cryptocurrency as a safe haven for whenever inflation picks up along with vaccinations and reduced Covid restrictions.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Buying cryptocurrency came with its own risks before, but with the technological advancements in firewall, it seems like a convenient way to store and profit one’s cash.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Elon Musk endorses Bitcoin</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In January, Elon Musk added #Bitcoin to his profile. This stamp of approval by the US tech giant entrepreneur validated the phenomenon which threw Bitcoin’s value through the roof! Later, Musk admitted to buying 1.5 billion USD worth of Bitcoins along with an announcement that customers would soon be able to purchase their Tesla via Bitcoin.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, in February, The New York Times covered a story and took a statement from US Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen, who termed Bitcoin as an inefficient way of transactions and seemed anxious as “potential losses investors could suffer” due to the unpredictable nature of the currency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'CRYPTOCURRENCIES TAKING HUGE STRIDES', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Apps,Crypto Mining News,Currency Market,news,popular', '1623070532_andre-francois-mckenzie-JrjhtBJ-pGU-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:55:32'),
(48, 'amazon-s-ceo-writes-his-annual-letter-to-the-shareholders', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 14:48:07 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since 1997, Jeff Bezos has been writing to his shareholders annually to relay Amazon’s numbers, vision, and future goals somewhat personally. As Amazon’s CEO prepares to step down and assume the role of executive chairman, Bezos announced he will make his company an employee-friendly company. As he would term it, “Earth’s Best Employer and Earth’s Safest Place to Work”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>World’s richest man has been under fire for not treating his employees humanely, especially during this devastating covid-19 pandemic. Several stories of employees being fired and cost-cutting schemes came out, bringing Amazon’s management of employees into question. Jeff Bezos is ready to assume the role of Executive Chairman this summer and he says he will focus his energy on promoting an employee-centric environment in his company.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In his <a href=\"https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/company-news/2020-letter-to-shareholders\">annual letter</a>, Bezos expressed pride in his company’s growth. He stated numbers that supported his behemoth empire of Amazon which doesn’t only include retail, but also Prime, Marketplace, Alexa, and AWS.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Amazon in 1997 and now…</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In his first letter to shareholders in 1997, Bezos writes, “Amazon had grown from having 158 employees to 614, and that we had surpassed 1.5 million customer accounts. We had just gone public at a split-adjusted stock price of $1.50 per share.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Comparing these numbers with numbers of 2020, he writes, “we hired 500,000 employees and now directly employ 1.3 million people around the world. We have more than 200 million Prime members worldwide. More than 1.9 million small and medium-sized businesses sell in our store, and they make up close to 60% of our retail sales. Customers have connected more than 100 million smart home devices to Alexa. Amazon Web Services serves millions of customers and ended 2020 with a $50 billion annualized run rate.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How much money his stakeholders made?</strong> He proudly states that Amazon generated $1.6 trillion of wealth for shareowners. As Amazon’s CEO prepares to develop a more employee-friendly persona, he made sure to point out how his company’s shareowners have been spending their fortune. Bezos continues to write in his letter that the stake owners “used their Amazon money for college, for emergencies, for houses, for vacations, to start their own business, for charity – and the list goes on.” He writes that this significant amount brings a positive change in their lives.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How this plays out for his employees?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jeff Bezos answered this question by looking at compensation expense. This means what the company spends here, goes to employees. He explains, “In 2020, employees earned $80 billion, plus another $11 billion to include benefits and various payroll taxes, for a total of $91 billion.” He describes Amazon’s relationship with employees in his letter too. He makes it clear that there are standards that the employees must meet which include training and certification. Just like any other company, employees have to check-in and check-out at their given time. Coaching is also provided to employees. Bezos explains it, “In fact, 82% of coaching is positive, provided to employees who are meeting or exceeding expectations.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Amazon’s CEO writes his Annual Letter to the Shareholders', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Don\'t Miss,Hot Updates,news,popular', '1623070517_money-6010251_1920.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:55:17'),
(49, 'nzdusd-ready-to-cross-0-72-level-later-this-year', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 15:09:57 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>USD is fighting hard to defeat NZD but just as expected, NZD has proven to be the Alpha of G10 pack. NZD is the strongest currency against USD in the G10 group and its future outlook is expected to become even stronger. After the results of Reserve Bank of New Zealand came out last night, NZD managed to secure a strong position in the market today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, in the shorter run, NZD might trade at a discount. Ned Rumpeltin, the European Head of FX strategies agreed to this claim in a recent interview stating that NZD outlook in the short term might reflect a lower trend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A brief analysis</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>NZDUSD is currently under bullish control and is headed towards the northern side. A major reason behind this upward move is the Reserve Bank of New Zealand that has proven its performance over the past few days. The policy makers have considered all possible external factors that could effect NZD and have come to the conclusion that Trans-Transman would reopen soon and the major economies are headed towards a stronger future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This conclusion has increased the confidence of investors in NZD and NZDUSD is going away from the bearish grip with every passing minute. However, it is interesting to note that the report shed light on the weaker domestic data which shows the possibility of a downfall due to the recent housing schemes announced by the government. If we talk about the medium term growth of NZDUSD, that wouldn\'t change much. The growth outlook as of now remains the same as February along with the Monetary Policy Statement.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The future of NZDUSD</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“NZD/USD made a clean break above resistance at the 0.7070 level in the aftermath of the policy decision.\" - FXM</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pair successfully broke the strong resistance level at 0.707 and is currently moving up towards the next stop that can be anywhere between 0.710-0.715. However, a strong resistance is expected at 0.71 level which would give a chance to the bears to take back control of the pair but it is important to remember that the actions of RBNZ and the improvement in the NZ economy wouldn\'t let the bears win easily. The natural market mechanisms are all in favor of the bulls and the pair seems to be indestructible for at least the next two weeks or so.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"In the absence of a clear positive catalyst, the kiwi could face a fairly tough slog from current levels.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand, NZD might face a short term decline if the economic conditions take a U-turn due to the third pandemic wave which is getting stronger day by day. In fact, the bullish fever might be shortlived and a bearish trap might come into existence.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interestingly, the current prediction for NZDUSD is around 0.72 level which is a chance for the bulls to maximize the profits before the pair goes into a depression period. However, anything above 0.72 would be considered an overbought trend and might lead towards a sudden failure causing the pair to crash.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t forget to share this article with your friends and family. Keep visiting us for more interesting content!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'NZDUSD ready to cross 0.72 level later this year', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates', '1623070491_macau-photo-agency-F36uIkMf-Gk-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:54:51'),
(50, 'bulls-are-ready-to-take-over-eurusd-soon', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 15:17:25 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EURUSD approached the 1.1992 level this Thursday and with a moderate bounce back, the pair now seems to be completely under the bullish control. EURUSD has been fighting to gain a position since the last few weeks and Interestingly, nor the bears or the bulls have been able to get a complete control of the pair but after a long fight, the bulls have finally managed to steal the thunder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, it is important to note that bears are still alive in the game and are giving a hard time to the bulls. The bears might steal away a possible victory from the bulls sooner or later. That being said, let\'s analyse the situation to understand the future outlook clearly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>US retail sales stats are out!</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The US retail sales report was revealed today and the details came out as a surprise. USA is finally recovering from the damages caused by covid19. The first wave was disastrous, the second wave passed quickly and the third wave was deadly for the US population as well as tbe US economy. Experts had predicted a sudden crash for the greenback but surprisingly USD came out stronger than expected.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The predicted US retail sales for March were 6.3% which wasn\'t easy to achieve and attracted many critics that drew a pessimistic image for USA but the report today silenced everyone when it revealed that US retail sales had grown to a huge 9.8% in March. Moreover, the unemployment report also complimented the US sales retail report. The predicted unemployment numbers were too high at the beginning of the 2021 but the numbers revealed last week showed a sharp decline to 683000. Furthermore, the Philadephia FED manufacturing report came out at 50.2 which further showed an improvement in the US economy. The next move for EURUSD will begin as the report for Industrial production and capacity utilisation will be published later this month.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As of now, the predicted results for the above mentioned reports are positive, keeping in mind the current trends of US economy which are pointing towards a better economy. In case of a downfall, the results might differ greatly but that won\'t be happening soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The EUR/USD pair retains its near-term bullish stance, as it consolidates at the upper end of its monthly range.” - FXS</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Right now the predicted levels for EURUSD are in favor of a bullish trend but a corrective action can be expected of the pair falls below 1.1940 in which case a sharp decline would be inevitable. However, the odds are in favor of the bulls and the predicted movement for the pair in the coming week is towards the 1.2010 level. If bulls are able to break the strong resistance level at this point, a medium term bullish trend would become certain in which case the bears would definitely lose big time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The European economy and US economy are both under the after effects of the third pandemic wave but the economies are improving gradually overtime. The predicted trends, however, are still in favor of the Euro and the greenback needs to fight hard in order to make a strong comeback.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more interesting content, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to shsre this article with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bulls are ready to take over EURUSD soon!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Hot Updates', '1623070478_hans-eiskonen-wn57cSQ7VzI-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:54:38'),
(51, 'audusd-down-again-are-bears-making-a-comeback', 'Tue, 20 Apr 2021 15:21:30 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AUDUSD has been enjoying a bullish ride since the beginning of this week but now as we move towards the end, the pair seems to be yet again influenced by the bears. The USD index has been struggling to gain a competitive position in the market and all rivals have taken advantage of it. First, USD was losing against GBP, then CAD and now AUD has decided to make a move. While the greenback has recovered and made a comeback against EUR and other competitors a few weeks ago, AUD seems to unaffected by it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you all know, greenback has dominated a majority since generations but after covid takeover, the US economy has faced huge losses and as a result USD kept on depreciating overtime. In fact, weaker currencies like PKR have been performing well against USD and have gained a lot since its fall in the recent economic conditions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AUD on the other hand has been in a moderate competition with USD since a very long time and the current scenario is in favor of it. The bulls are looking to make a longterm influence on the pair and till now they\'ve been quite successful.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Where is AUDUSD headed?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The AUDUSD pair reached a new high earlier today around 0.7760 and declared its vote in favor of the bulls. The bears however have been fighting hard to pull it down but their efforts seem worthless. It is interesting to note that the bears did manage to take control of the AUDUSD pair during the American session today when they were able to drag it down to 0.7745 level. Some investors have seen this movement as a threat and a potential rebound and many analysts are calling it a corrective action as a result of an overbought trend but what exactly is the reality?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Well, if we look at the bigger picture, AUDUSD is already under a strong bullish influence and even though it lost 0.2% in value today, the pair is still 100 pips higher on the weekly chart which may indicate an overbought trend. Having said that, at the current position AUDUSD seems to be heading north. The pair is expected to cross 0.7780 level in the coming week and only then would be a corrective action inevitable. The US dollar index is still struggling to make a rebound but is failing miserably so for now, the bullish AUDUSD trend is safe from a potential bearish attack.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>University of Michigan revealed its latest data earlier today which claimed an improvement in Consumer Sentiment Index to 86.5 from the previous 84.9. The index showed a positive future outlook but in reality it was way below the predicted 89.6 level due to which no real market reaction was triggered in favor of the greenback. The trends right now are not in any way in favor of the US economy and greenback continues to decline.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To conclude, AUDUSD is headed north and it is a perfect opportunity for the bulls to maximize. The bears would need to play a safe game in order to survive.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more interesting content, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to share it with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'AUDUSD down again - Are bears making a comeback?', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,News &amp; Updates', '1623070457_money-6010251_1920.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:54:17'),
(52, 'e-yuan-is-not-a-threat-to-replace-dollar-china', 'Mon, 26 Apr 2021 11:47:06 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One cannot omit China when discussing the digitization of anything and everything. The recent news in the market has highlighted that China will be digitizing its currency, i.e. the Yuan could be replaced from paper money to binary code soon, making China become the first country to achieve this milestone. China has been working on e-yuan since 2014, deploying various testing and trial phases in different cities. E-yuan is effectively being tested in 11 cities now, as a pilot program. The ‘Developing country’- China has been far ahead in digital transactions than the developed western countries. With money apps like ‘Wechat pay’ and ‘Alipay’ becoming popular and mainstream ways of not only paying monthly bills, tuition fees, and even buying a banana, more and more Chinese people have stopped carrying wallets altogether. Barcode transactions are everywhere; from a small-time peanut vendor to a luxury store of Gucci!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Biden administration is cautious…</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>… rather, Joe Biden’s administration is threatened! The United States of America maintains its status as a world superpower because the dollar is the international standard of currency and all trade is done with it. China is on its way to becoming a superpower, but it cannot hold the status until the dollar is toppled by the Chinese yuan as the market leader. The Biden administration is keeping a close eye on the development of e-yuan, making sure the dollar’s reign is not overthrown. To not let the USA’s fire go further up in flames, the Deputy Governor of People’s Bank of China has given the assurance that mainstreaming the use of e-yuan is not meant to replace the status of the US dollar globally, but it is only intended for domestic use. <a href=\"https://www.trendsmap.com/twitter/tweet/1383804071895715844\">Li Bao reassured</a> on Sunday that the internationalization of the Chinese yuan will happen naturally and in its due course of time, “I think our goal is to allow the market to choose, to facilitate international trade and investment.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With cryptocurrencies making headlines of going public in the US stock exchange, pressure for e-yuan to internationalize gets more urgent. Bitcoin, doge coin could face serious competition from China’s digital currency, and the People’s Bank of China will be the first major central bank to lift off e-currency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>e-yuan is only meant for domestic use…</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It could be a sugar-coated pat on the shoulder so the Biden administration can back off. How so? China plans to open e-yuan for cross-border use for the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics. It could not only be used by local athletes but also foreign athletes. One must keep in mind that the largest retailing sites internationally, after Amazon, are Chinese! Alibaba, Daraz, JD, and more are Chinese. If China opens the e-yuan as a standard currency to buy and sell on its retailing websites, it will open a massive influx of foreign currency exchange, boosting yuan traded globally.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, there is a brighter side to the picture for the US. In a vast market environment, foreign ownership of Chinese bonds and stocks is relatively low rounding to 3% and 5%, respectively. While the yuan\'s share of global payments and central bank reserves is still only about 2%!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'e-Yuan is not a threat to replace Dollar: China', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Mining News,Currency Market', '1623070441_sharon-mccutcheon-ZihPQeQR2wM-unsplash-1.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:54:01');
