(65, 'turkish-lira-reaches-lowest-watermark-of-2021', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 11:38:17 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another political shift has pushed the Turkish lira to dip at its lowest rate in 2021, so far. The rise of a dispute with ex-US president, Donald Trump, ignited a recession and put Lira in a state of crisis back in 2018. Turkey has been having an unstable foreign relation with the United States of America and Istanbul’s assets are heavily reliant on Washington. As a basic mathematical equation would suggest, Istanbul is having unstable economic conditions since. Biden fulfilled his campaign promise to Armenian-Americans and recognized the killings of millions of Armenians in the Ottoman Empire as genocide. This has not only strained already strained relations with Turkey but also catapulted Istanbul towards Moscow. Turkey criticized that the move has “undermined trust and friendship”. Ibrahim Kalin also expressed frustration to Reuters News Agency that Washington is behaving irresponsibly and recognition of Armenia’s genocide means Biden is trying to, “artificially undermine ongoing relationships for narrow political agendas.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What about the Turkish Lira and Assets?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In emerging markets of 2021, the Turkish Lira has been performing the worst so far. Monday saw it come close to its record low in the market when it touched 8.425 against the US dollar. Turkish Lira was at its lowest last November when it recorded 8.58 versus the US dollar. After Biden’s official recognition of the Armenian genocide on Saturday, Lira lost 3.5 percent in the last three trading days. The reason behind this dip is not only the strained relation with Washington. Recep Tayyip Erdogan appointed a new central bank chief, Sahap Kavcioglu, a month ago. Kavcioglu announced higher interest rates would hurt the economy and he would keep the monetary policy constricted… for now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Erdogan appointed Kavcioglu after sacking a respected policy watchman, Naci Agbal. This move plunged Lira as low as 15%. Kavcioglu is as conservative as Erdogan when it comes to policymaking and both believe that higher interest rates should be avoided. However, Agbal had designed a monetary policy where the interest rate was raised to 19% to curtail inflation when it was at 16%. Experts and analysts predict inflation to go as high as a whopping 18% since Kavcioglu would follow an orthodox policy of selling foreign reserves to keep the inflation rate under control. Foreign investors are not happy with Erdogan’s decision of changing central bank governors. They sold their Turkish assets when Agbal was sacked.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2019 and 2020, Turkey witnessed a sharp decline in its foreign reserves which accounted for at least 128 billion dollars. The opposition has brought this rapid depletion into question and has asked for an explanation since it was backed by the central bank. The New Central Bank’s chief has defended this move by saying that the Turkish Lira would have depreciated to record lows if foreign reserves were not sold as rapidly as they did. He related to bad examples of 20 years ago when corporate went bankrupt since Lira could not be engineered to rise and compete in the international market; “You need to meet the FX demand of last year, if you don’t, Turkey would have to face the consequences.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Turkish Lira Reaches Lowest Watermark Of 2021', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Uncategorized', '1623069939_omid-armin-DVi5c4Tr4cA-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:45:39'),
(66, 'ethereum-setting-new-price-records', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 11:42:40 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the past few years, digital currency or cryptocurrency has taken a stronghold all across the globe. This currency has taken over the market with its strong price and changing trends. While everything is getting digitized, the currency is also following the developments. The majority of cryptocurrencies were launched in the market almost a decade ago. The initial coins that were launched in the market were Bitcoin, Ethereum, LiteCoin, Polka Dot, and many others. The initial prices of these coins were so low that people were afraid to invest their money into them but in the past few years, the currency started to get some fame and gained a prominent position in the stock market. The most famous cryptocurrency being Bitcoin, which was once only $35, jumped to thousands and has now touched the heights of $45,000. This grasped the investor’s attention, and they decided to jump into this plunge inviting them to invest their money to buy shares in cryptocurrency. It was the tenure before the pandemic when the prices in the global stock market started changing they saw massive fluctuations in the prices and their values took a new growth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><strong>Ethereum touching the heights</strong></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last time, Dogecoin was the most talked-about cryptocurrency due to Elon Musk, who tweeted about this coin and it was then considered one of the favorite and most considered coins. But in the past 24 hours, a major variability was seen in the cryptocurrency market when the most famous currency spotlight was taken by Ethereum. Last night it was observed that the price of Ethereum reached the maximum limit to date, recorded to be $2789. This has been the ground-breaking price of Ethereum since its launch. $40.18 billion were invested and this was the biggest market cap covered by this coin in the past few years. According to the statistics, the increment in the price was over 3.178%, which marks as, by far, the biggest gap covered by any currency in the market.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><strong>Major Cryptocurrency trading</strong></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we look at the recent trends of various cryptocurrencies, all the small currencies started to become dominant. It is a record after August 2018, when the cryptocurrency price started deteriorating and it dropped to a total of 50% of the total amount since 3 years. This is considered as a major setback to bitcoin which it has faced and a continuous drop is witnessed in its price. Ethereum was showing a major fluctuation in its statistical chart for a few weeks but yesterday was a remarkable day where it touched the sky. Many other coins have seen a boost in which Stellar, Cardano, XRP, and Polka Dot have shown a massive change in the statistics. According to various reports, it is speculation where people are expecting that shortly there will be a time where Ethereum is going to compete with bitcoin and there are analysts who believe that it will surpass the amount of Bitcoin and will lead the charts which will be a big upset for these cryptocurrencies.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ethereum Setting New Price Records', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Mining News,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates', '1623069788_pexels-moose-photos-1036637.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:43:08'),
(67, 'global-chip-shortage-dropping-sales-halting-production', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 11:44:26 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can claim to be a psychic now since you can probably predict all news are about covid-19, indirectly, if not directly. Covid-19 has toppled routine businesses, lives, manufacturing, sales, health, and menial tasks globally! What has covid-19 brought to us now? A semiconductor chip shortage. With the majority of the world working from home and starting businesses digitally, there is a vivid imbalance between the demand and supply ratio of chips. These tiny things carry within them a world of digital necessities required in laptops, work stations, automobiles, wireless communications, wired communication, mobile phones, gaming consoles, smartwatches, and whatnot! Talk about living in the digital age! The human’s reliance on chips has brought upon an unprecedented scarcity in attaining them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The world’s largest chip maker, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co Ltd (TSMC), had opened 2021 with 19.4% profit in sales in the first quarter. However, they have also raised the alarm of not being able to meet the demands of companies that use chips in their electronics fearing to bring billions of dollars of lost-in-sale products.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Phone Manufacturers in Trouble:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Top global mobile phone manufacturers, Apple Inc. and Samsung Electronics Co. are also gearing up to face losses and less production output than projected for the year. Ironically these companies are now under pressure; the same companies enjoyed massive profits in sales during the pandemic as more and more consumers turned to them to equip their households and livelihoods on their electronics. Apple’s top-selling products; iPads and Macs, are now in challenging waters as sales are crimping and shortage on shelves is visible. After a chartbuster second quarter, the Apple CFO Maestri fears that this situation will shave 3 billion dollars to 4 billion dollars off of the revenue during the fiscal third quarter this year. Global shipments rose to 27% to 347 million devices on average in the first quarter but a shortage of chip components could bring that thrust to rest in the remaining months of 2021.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Apple’s toughest contender Samsung has also braced itself for impact. Bear in mind that Samsung not only uses chips but also produces them. Even then, the future of revenue generation seems bleak. Samsung has also predicted a decline this quarter as the demand for their top-selling product, the Samsung Galaxy smartphone is not like before.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Car Manufacturers on Brakes</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An unprecedented shortage of chips has affected the automobile industry since this digital age has put this powerful component under the hoods of many cars. This is bringing production at plants to a halt. Tesla was the first company to suspend production due to this supply shock. Honda Motor Co. is preparing to suspend production for almost a week in Japan next month, BMW AG is planning to hold its Mini car production in Britain, while Ford Motor Co. has already projected a decline in their sales graph of this year and it could go well into 2022. Collectively speaking, the automobile industry is feared to face 61 billion dollars in lost sales this year.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Global Chip Shortage; Dropping Sales, Halting Production', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,News &amp; Updates', '1623069768_martin-sanchez-VhjsGKMefkk-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:42:48'),
(68, 'giant-companies-warn-of-burden-on-consumer-s-wallet', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 11:53:00 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re thinking of wiping your nose with a tissue, think again. Kleenex, wipes, tissue rolls are going to be expensive this year and will continue to be in 2022. Not just wipes and tissue, even cereal, plastic, sugar, paper, grain, and fizzy drinks are going to cost consumers more. The reason behind the price hike of common commodities is, ironically, a rarity of the raw materials. Pandemic has hit us hard globally; disturbance in demand and supply ratio, congestion at ports, delay in shipments, rise in fuel prices have forced mega-companies to raise prices of everyday essentials to cover their product portfolios.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Major companies and distributors like Procter &amp; Gamble, Coca-Cola, and Kimberly Clark have already raised the alarm that they are set to put a burden on the consumer’s wallets as they hustle to get their hands on raw material and get their shipment across on time. Congestion at ports is not helping with timely distribution to stores. Parents with quarantined babies are also about to have a harder time managing their finances since basic baby products are going to be more expensive. Diapers, baby food, and baby wipes will remain expensive in 2022 as well.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Demand outpacing supply:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the US economy is stabilizing again after being hit hard by the pandemic, this news comes as another shock to citizens. The US faced one of the hardest times with Covid, with reports of increasing deaths and cases day by day. Just in January this year, a number of daily new cases reached a staggering figure of 300,669. Vaccination drive is also moving along at a steady pace, while experts are of the opinion that the rollout is rather slow. States have started to lift restrictions and businesses are reopening. Businesses that are reopening have a pressure of supplying to the pent-up demand of customers, but they are not getting their supplies, which is causing problems countrywide. Data from NielsenIQ reveals that over the past few months, prices of everyday commodities, like toilet paper, have increased modestly.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The scarcity of raw materials has resulted in an increase in prices as well. General Mills, which makes popular cereal ‘Cheerios’, has announced it is also considering raising prices since sugar, grain and other raw materials become inadequate and expensive. Kleenex and toilet paper producers, Kimberley Clark, has also made it known to consumers that it plans to offset the impact of higher raw material prices and price hike will cover about 60% of their product portfolio. Behemoth Company, Coca-Cola is also raising the costs of their beverages. Similarly, Proctor &amp; Gamble is set to charge consumers more for their feminine care, baby care, and adult care products. According to data available to the public, “US consumer prices increased a sharp 0.6 percent in March, the biggest uptick since 2012, while inflation over the past year jumped 2.6 percent.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wall Street had predicted that inflation would be the tough result of the pandemic as the economy would stabilize.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Giant Companies Warn Of Burden on Consumer’s Wallet', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates', '1623069731_imelda-GcnPjvqRL18-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:42:11'),
(69, 'new-midday-stock-market-changes', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 11:55:05 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since the pandemic has invaded this world, there has been a massive upheaval in the stock market. Many big names have lost their position, while a lot of big names have changed their statistical position in the market. There was a time when the pandemic was at its peak and the stock market crashed, not once, but many times and the global process of shares in the market collapsed. At that time there was no hope that the market will regain its position again in the near future. This situation changed the ratios of the world stock market. However, in the current times, another midday drastic change has been observed in the stock market where a big fluctuation in the prices of shares of various leading companies was witnessed, which lead to high activation of points in the stock market.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Social Media Giants leading the market</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was observed in the midday that the trading shares gained a sudden boost, and that was of all about the big names of social media and e-platforms including Amazon, Twitter followed by Chevron, Colgate Palmolive, and Newell Brands. It was observed that the e-commerce giant- Amazon saw a sudden increment in its shares of about 1%. According to the various statistical firms, the gain in the market shares observed have been triple in the first half of the year, equating to the price of $8.1million, however, the sale price of all the shares increased to 44% making up to $108million as a sum total.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The second upheaval in the market which was observed the market was of Twitter, with its shares showing a rapid boost with record-breaking sales in the midday market of 13%, which is by far the maximum attained price record of the company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Field Companies chasing the Social media giants</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not only the e-based firms but the field firms who have established themselves in the market for a long time have been in this chase as well. From Skyworks solution to Chevron to Colgate Palmolive, all these have seen a drastic boom in their shares as well. These are the record-breaking stats of this year where the market has seen a growth in the developing businesses which have increased the value of the companies as well as their global shares.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we look at the statistics of Chevron, it has a dipped out to the increment of 3% in the first quarter which itself is an achievement and they were capable enough to develop a strong business by attaining 90% shares in total. Similarly, Skyworks Solutions have attained 8% midday sales and earning 2 cents on each share of $2.37. These are the record-breaking stats ever seen in the market after the pandemic. The market analysts are hopeful that this midday sale is the path-opener for a new era where shares will set a good benchmark and profiting the company as well as boosting the global economy. This will be a good time for all the investors to hop in and gather a good amount of money.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'New Midday Stock Market Changes', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,News &amp; Updates,Social Media', '1623069696_merakist-CNbRsQj8mHQ-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:41:36'),
(70, 'ethereum-sets-a-new-high-record-a-longterm-bullish-trend-expected', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 22:44:12 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>World\'s second largest cryptocurrency, Ethereum just made a new world record earlier today. After Bitcoin, Ethereum now seems to be the next big thing in the digital world. Ethereum has the second largest market capitalization across the globe and it is now aiming to get on top. The sudden upwards movement has caught the attention of investors throughout the globe and it is safe to say that the future trends of Ethereum would be under complete bullish control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Will Ethereum take over Bitcoin? Will Ethereum become the new Crypto Champ? Let\'s find out!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Behind the scenes</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ethereum is one of the most popular cryptocurrencies and holds high value. Recently, the European Investment Bank held a press conference in which it announced its latest plans. The bank is planning to introduce a Digital Bond that would run on the Ethereum blockchain network and would be distributed, first locally and then in the future internationally (unofficial). The announcement made by the bank pumped energy into Ethereum and the cryptocurrency went flying up in the sky with bulls controlling the journey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was reported on Bloomberg on Tuesday that EIB has decided to introduce a 100 million euro digital bond. Such a huge amount would be favorable for a bullish field and Ethereum would be looking at new yearly highs. The sale of this bond would be managed by the famous Goldman Sachs, Banco Santander and Societe Generale. Together they will make sure that all transactions are handled flawlessly and there\'s no room for fraud of any kind. It is interesting to note that Goldman Sachs have been a part of major controversy back in 2008 but ironically it is a major entity that would be handling all future transactions related to the 100 million euro digital bonds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After this announcement was made, a strong push was experienced by Ethereum which went high up to the 2713.95 mark and claimed its new record position on Wednesday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The recent announcement by EIB has \"triggered a bullish institutional use case for ethereum\" - Danny Kim (SFOX)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Talking about the current Ethereum supply in the market, he added:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The amount of ethereum sitting on exchanges continues to drop lower and has been the lowest in the past year, with less supply on exchange available, there\'s less likely a chance of a major sell-off.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to lower supply, the demand for Ethereum has risen greatly over the past few days which will add up to the price increase and cause an even stronger bullish trend. Ethereum is used by many gamers around the world to buy virtual items. It is the only cryptocurrency that is widely accepted my most game developers.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, the bullish trend was further strengthened after JP Morgan showed interest during its latest announcement on Tuesday morning in which they hinted towards introducing a bitcoin managed fund system. This announcement opened gates for all other cryptocurrencies as well, which now consider this as an opportunity to enter in other financial market types.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ethereum is currently aiming towards a new high record and it is an ideal time to buy it before the bears make a comeback sooner or later. For more interesting content, keep visiting our website. Help us grow by sharing this article with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ethereum sets a new high record - A longterm bullish trend expected', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Mining News,Currency Market,News &amp; Updates', '1623069627_cryptocurrency-3409658_640.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:40:27'),
(71, 'usdjpy-climbs-north-as-us-treasury-yields-recover', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 22:57:22 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The USDJPY pair edged higher today after a week of bearish domination and is now having a positive outlook for the coming weeks. The US treasury bond yield has started making a recovery and it is interesting to note that the yield percentage has been moving upwards since the last 3 days. Last week, the yield was moving in an opposite direction and greenback was under pressure, failing miserably against its rival currencies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The DXY has been down throughout the month of April and the yields have been unstable. Investors have lost confidence in USD which has lead to a sharp decline for the greenback and the economy continues to suffer. As expected, the ripple effect of these movements have now caused Wall Street to decline as well. Earlier today, the Wall Street indexes showed moderate losses which rang an alarm for investors in favor of the greenback. The results caused a panic throughout the globe and as expected, USD came crashing down again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This was not the case on Friday. USDJPY was completely under a bearish influence but it managed to make a comeback on Monday morning which was maintained till Tuesday afternoon. The pair is currently up by 0.35% which indicates a bullish trend for the next 3 trading days. The pair reached it new daily highs at 108.48 level and is currently trading around 108.45 level. The minor loss is due to the natural mechanism but the pair is still expected to travel north during the next few weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>A positive outlook for USDJPY</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The US treasury bond yields have finally managed to edge closer to the set benchmark and the previous 2 days have been pure luck. The yield moved up by almost 2% and is currently higher by a huge 1.15% margin yielding at around 1.58%. This move was a surprise for not just the bears but also for the bulls who had been stuck in the bearish trap since last week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, Wall Street posted losses during the American session earlier today. The declining Wall Street indexes helped the greenback to maintain its position against its rivals. Furthermore, DXY has been showing signs of improvement and is currently up by 0.1% at around 90.92 level. The Bank of Japan has decided to leave its policies unchanged for now and the Governor has declared to ease down the Monetary policies which was pre-decided during the last board meeting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Simultaneously, the Conference Board Committee\'s consumer confidence index declared positive results which further pushed USDJPY upwards. The board results showed an improvement towards 121.7 in the month of April which was way above the expected 113 mark. Even though it was a major movement towards the better side, the mechanism failed to trigger any kind of market reaction which helped the pair maintain its bullish journey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Having said that, investors will now have to keep an eye on the Retail Trade Data that is being released tomorrow in Japan to predict the life of the current bullish trend that seems to be in the strongest position right now. We can\'t say anything for sure yet but a wild guess would be that the pair is aiming towards a new monthly high.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more interesting content, keep visiting our website and don\'t forget to share it with your friends and family before leaving!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'USDJPY climbs North as US treasury yields recover', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,Investment,News &amp; Updates', '1623069561_pepi-stojanovski-MJSFNZ8BAXw-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:39:21'),
(72, 'nasdaq-s-p-500-ready-to-set-a-new-high-record-this-week', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 22:59:05 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>NASDAQ and S&amp;P 500 have been aiming towards north since last week but due to weakening US economy their movements were trapped in the bearish regions. However, the scenario took a sharp turn on Thursday and NASDAQ along with S&amp;P 500 is now flying towards the North!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you know why?</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Well, when Apple and Facebook join hands, who can stop the index from rising? That\'s exactly what happened today. NASDAQ experienced a quick upwards movement as soon as the tech report was revealed. The report showed a great improvement in the tech industry and the generated revenues were more than what the forecasted statements talked about.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A major chunk of these earnings belonged to Facebook and Apple inc. Some analysts have been labeling the two giants as a lifesaving injection for NASDAQ while others talk about the expected longterm bullish trends that have begun today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>AAPL and FB to the rescue!</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Apple revealed its revenue reports earlier today and the results were way ahead of Wall Street\'s expectations, thanks to Mac and iPhone. The company gained a 1% in value after the reports were made public and the trends continue to move towards the bullish regions. It is now expected that Apple would gain anywhere between 1.5%-2.2% during next week. NASDAQ and S&amp;P 500 seems to be recovering finally and the pressure has eased down a bit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Apple claimed a daily high record, Facebook was aiming much higher. The reports revealed by FB showed an improvement in the quarterly revenues and the net profits calculated during the given accounting period. After revelation of such positive future outlook, Facebook set a new record by gaining 6.6% in value. A major reason behind the higher revenues and improved net profit was an increase in ad spending that was noticed during quarantine. With more demand, the prices followed the natural mechanism and went higher, resulting in a better quarterly profit for the company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a result S&amp;P 500 claimed higher position in the market by moving up 2.4% on the basis of Facebook revenue reports. This sector of S&amp;P 500 is now in the lead against all other 11 S&amp;P sectors and the predicted future trends show a clear dominance as of now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"We expected tech earnings to come in strong and they comfortably cleared the high bar which is extremely impressive. But also, it is another sign just how quickly this economy continues to roar back,\" </em>- Ryan Detrick, LPL Financial Marketing strategist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The US government has been working hard to overcome the damage done by Covid19 and has been successful in aiding household schemes along with major businesses. The unemployment has reduced over the past few weeks and the economy seems to be making a comeback. A total of 553000 individuals applied for unemployment benefits last week compared to earlier week\'s 566000 figure which shows that slowly and steadily the economic conditions are improving.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tech industry is flourishing and NASDAQ has already made a rebound earlier today. The expected future outlook seems to be under control of the bulls and now is the right time to invest in the right stocks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For more interesting analysis, keep visiting our website. Help us grow by sharing our content with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'NASDAQ, S&P 500 ready to set a new high record this week!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Currency Market,Economics,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates', '1623069533_meric-dagli-XR5Fudiw1Z4-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:38:53'),
(73, 'bears-are-ready-to-pull-usd-back-for-the-fourth-consecutive-week', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 23:09:40 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The dollar is under heavy bearish pressure and the bulls can\'t do much about it. Greenback has been fighting against the market mechanism since the last 3 weeks in order to claim its lost position. Unfortunately, it has failed miserably. After a strong fight put up by the bulls, greenback finally got trapped in the bear\'s den and bulls had to accept a temporary defeat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greenback is suffering some major losses and investors are now uncomfortable. Many have lost confidence in the US economy. The only reason behind the Southern USD journey&nbsp; is the implementation of wrong policies at the wrong time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>US dollar gained some ground on Friday during the American session but it remained near the multi-lows that have been consistently damaging the greenback since the last 4 weeks now. All credit goes to the dovish monetary policy being implemented in the United States despite a recovering economy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is true that the dovish policy was ideal during the early pandemic situation but right now the economy seems to be on the right track and the US needs to get rid of this policy if it wants to gain the confidence of the investors again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What to expect from the greenback?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yesterday, at around 2:55 AM ET, DXY edged a little higher, adding a 0.1% gain to the index value. The dollar index consists of 6 rival currencies and is currently maintained at 90.648 mark. Even though this, apparently, seems like an improvement, the index has ended 0.2% lower on the weekly charts. The accumulated losses for April have now equalled 2.8% which shows the kind of pressure USD is in. If the losing streak continues during the 4th week as well, it will then become the longest losing streak for USD since July\'s 6 week slide.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we look at the bigger picture, the dovish policy is not the only element responsible for the losses of the dollar. Other rival commodity currencies have started performing well over the past few weeks, since the overall economic conditions are improving throughout the globe now. The demand for industrial and agricultural goods have increased which pushed their prices higher and as a result the commodity currencies gained in value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best performing currencies against the dollar this week have been CAD and NZD. It wasn\'t a surprise at all, the trend analysis of last week predicted this outcome and the bullish journey for these currencies won\'t end too early.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to these currencies, other major rivals are also giving a tough time to the greenback. The EURUSD pair is trading with a 0.1% loss at around 1.2113 while GBPUSD is consistent at 1.3942 level. USDJPY is declining and is right now trading at the 108.77 level with a 0.1% loss whereas, surprisingly, the silent pair AUDUSD has risen by 0.2% during the past week and is currently trading at 0.7779 level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The dollar is under heavy bearish pressure and the bulls can\'t do much about it. Greenback has been fighting against the market mechanism since the last 3 weeks in order to claim its lost position. Unfortunately, it has failed miserably. After a strong fight put up by the bulls, greenback finally got trapped in the bear\'s den and bulls had to accept a temporary defeat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The greenback is suffering some major losses and investors are now uncomfortable. Many have lost confidence in the US economy. The only reason behind the Southern USD journey is the implementation of wrong policies at the wrong time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>US dollar gained some ground on Friday during the American session but it remained near the multi-lows that have been consistently damaging the greenback since the last 4 weeks now. All credit goes to the dovish monetary policy being implemented in the United States despite a recovering economy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is true that the dovish policy was ideal during the early pandemic situation but right now the economy seems to be on the right track and the US needs to get rid of this policy if it wants to gain the confidence of the investors again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What to expect from the greenback?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yesterday, at around 2:55 AM ET, DXY edged a little higher, adding a 0.1% gain to the index value. The dollar index consists of 6 rival currencies and is currently maintained at 90.648 mark. Even though this, apparently, seems like an improvement, the index has ended 0.2% lower on the weekly charts. The accumulated losses for April have now equalled 2.8% which shows the kind of pressure USD is in. If the losing streak continues during the 4th week as well, it will then become the longest losing streak for USD since July\'s 6 week slide.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we look at the bigger picture, the dovish policy is not the only element responsible for the losses of the dollar. Other rival commodity currencies have started performing well over the past few weeks, since the overall economic conditions are improving throughout the globe now. The demand for industrial and agricultural goods have increased which pushed their prices higher and as a result the commodity currencies gained in value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best performing currencies against the dollar this week have been CAD and NZD. It wasn\'t a surprise at all, the trend analysis of last week predicted this outcome and the bullish journey for these currencies won\'t end too early.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to these currencies, other major rivals are also giving a tough time to the greenback. The EURUSD pair is trading with a 0.1% loss at around 1.2113 while GBPUSD is consistent at 1.3942 level. USDJPY is declining and is right now trading at the 108.77 level with a 0.1% loss whereas, surprisingly, the silent pair AUDUSD has risen by 0.2% during the past week and is currently trading at 0.7779 level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The predicted outlook of USD is quite pessimistic and next week would be once again dominated by the bears. The greenback is expected to set a new low record before a corrective trend would appear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep visiting our website for more interesting analysis. Help us grow by sharing this article with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to these currencies, other major rivals are also giving a tough time to the greenback. The EURUSD pair is trading with a 0.1% loss at around 1.2113 while GBPUSD is consistent at 1.3942 level. USDJPY is declining and is right now trading at the 108.77 level with a 0.1% loss whereas, surprisingly, the silent pair AUDUSD has risen by 0.2% during the past week and is currently trading at 0.7779 level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The predicted outlook of USD is quite pessimistic and next week would be once again dominated by the bears. The greenback is expected to set a new low record before a corrective trend would appear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep visiting our website for more interesting analysis. Help us grow by sharing this article with your friends and family!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bears are ready to pull USD back for the fourth consecutive week!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Currency Market,News &amp; Updates', '1623069514_meric-dagli-XR5Fudiw1Z4-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:38:34'),
(74, 'bitcoin-is-now-aiming-towards-60000-bears-under-pressure', 'Tue, 04 May 2021 23:11:46 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitcoin has been hammered by the bears during the last few weeks and now it has finally decided to come out of the bearish pressure. The morning of 30th April wasn\'t an ideal morning for BTC. The crypto king was constantly being pulled down by the bears and investors were losing confidence with every passing minute.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Experts were predicting a BTC trend anywhere between $45000 and $49000 by the end of the day. However, as they say, Forex is unpredictable; in a matter of seconds, Bitcoin decided to say NO to the bearish torture and the rest was history. At $53000 level, the bulls finally came to rescue the king of all cryptocurrencies and that is how BTC found a strong support that remained undefeated till the end of the day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that Bitcoin is being supported by the bulls, the future outlook has once again changed and experts are predicting a journey towards North.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Will Bitcoin maintain its Bullish journey? Let\'s find out!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Next stop: $60,000 in 1 week</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our daily analysis shows a positive future trend for Bitcoin and if we talk about April 30, Bitcoin ended up higher than the previous days. Even though the ending point was lower than the opening mark, Bitcoin showed signs of improvement and is now expected to continue its journey upwards. Here are the expected resistance and support levels for next week:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Support levels: $51000, $49000, $47000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Resistance levels: $56000, $58500, $61000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While chances of a bearish takeover are quite thin at this stage, a fall to the support levels mentioned above is expected. Having said that, Bitcoin\'s longterm journey is predicted to touch all three resistance levels mentioned above and if Bitcoin crosses $61000, it won\'t stop before nearing the 70k mark.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But to make that a reality, bitcoin would first have to reclaim its lost resistance levels that were noted at $54500 and $54834 earlier this month. If Bitcoin fails to reclaim these positions then a bullish trend won\'t take place, in fact a bearish grip would pull BTC below $50000 during the next 2 weeks. Another obstacle would arise if BTC crosses the lost resistance levels and reaches the $55000 mark. The bulls will then have to nake sure that the crypto king crosses this level otherwise all efforts would be wasted in a matter of days.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The RSI(14), however, confirms a bullish trend during the next few days. The current trends are likely to push BTC above the 21 day moving average points which would then lead Bitcoin across the $60000 mark.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Conclusion&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cryptocurrencies have been gaining value since the last few months. Previously, we wrote an article on Ethereum which was rising gradually, XRP has been moving up as well and now Bitcoin has joined the trend.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In short, cryptocurrencies are back in action and now is the time to invest in favor of the bulls in order to maximize profits in May. The bulls are clearly the champions right now.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep visiting our website for more interesting articles, don\'t forget to subscribe before leaving!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bitcoin is now aiming towards $60000 - Bears under pressure!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Mining News,News &amp; Updates', '1623069478_dmitry-demidko-OG3A-ilG8AY-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:37:58'),
(75, 'the-us-china-recover-as-europe-s-economy-shrinks', 'Mon, 10 May 2021 13:45:52 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the first quarter of 2021 came to an end, reports of economic conditions rolled in. Condition of 19 European countries which also use Euros as their currency does not look good due to a number of reasons which will be listed in this article. It is, however, safe to say that Europe is not doing well in comparison to the two largest global economies, China and the US, which are already on their way to recovery. China was the only country with the largest growing economy in 2020. The United States was hit hard by the pandemic and lagged behind, but 2021 saw a positive change as it lifted restrictions and rolled out vaccines at a steady pace. Figures released this Thursday showed that the US economy grew by 1.6 percent in the first quarter of this year. Fiscal support in the shape of a relief package of 1.9 trillion US dollars along with earlier support packages helped US citizens’ large majority to stay above the poverty line. Another evidence of US economic recovery is the latest unemployment rate falling to 6.0 percent after peaking to a high 14.8 percent during the worst conditions brought by the pandemic. China was hit first and hard with the novel coronavirus but was quick to overcome and recover due to harsh lockdown, punishable restrictions, and fast vaccine rollout.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>So, what’s happening in Europe?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Europe is far behind in vaccine distribution than China and the US. This has resulted in lockdowns of longer durations, affecting livelihoods and businesses. Prolonged lockdowns are not helping the economy to get back to its feet, a major reason for lagging behind. Europe did well from July to September last year, however, after failing to maintain its economic growth, experts fear the continent has fallen back into recession in the second straight quarter. Some European countries’ stats show hope in surviving the recession in the second quarter of 2021. France, for example, showed an unprecedented growth of 0.4 percent compared to the previous quarter. Europe’s largest economy, Germany, showed an unexpected shrink in its economy. A whopping 1.7 percent negative surprise as travel, tourism, and manufacturing industries failed to perform up to par. The imbalanced ratio of supply and demand hit the manufacturing industry hard. France and Hungary, on the other hand, show promise of positive growth in May as they house the largest vaccinated population of the continent, and distribution is continuing at a steady, stable pace. Their government is ready to open outdoor dining, terrace cafes, cinemas, galleries, museums, and theatres under specific protocols on 19<sup>th</sup> May. However, their hospitals are also having a high number of hospitalized corona patients.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Greece, Italy, and Spain are Mediterranean countries that rely heavily on tourism. The number of travellers to these three countries dropped as low as 75 percent since the pandemic! Greece has lifted lockdown restrictions partially for member countries of the European Union in hopes of generating some revenue during the devastating pandemic. European countries will need a better plan and financial support programs to survive the recession.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The US, China Recover As Europe’s Economy Shrinks', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Economics', '1623069455_alex-vasey-3lxrM5yvkcI-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:37:35');
