(101, 'alibaba-s-rival-may-surpass-it-in-the-e-commerce-space', 'Tue, 01 Jun 2021 12:52:40 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the world of commerce in the year 1998, an e-commerce company landed a newbie with the name- Alibaba. Jack Ma, the owner of Alibaba, revolutionized the world of business on the internet. The e-commerce industry saw a big change where everything got available for trade online. Within no time, all your goods and necessities of life were ready to be ordered from any part of the globe and delivered at your doorstep through shopping on the internet. After establishing the name in this field, various other companies emerged but none gained the fame that Alibaba received. The total business that Alibaba has managed to make in this field over the years sums up to be an amount of S109.480 billion, making Jack Ma one of the richest people in the world. However, with time, many of the competitors that emerged as serious competition to Alibaba in the market vanished, none qualifying enough to compete with Alibaba, except one- JD.com.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>JD has established itself in this field effectively and has set big goals for itself. Over the years, these two companies have gone neck to neck in the market; the shares, market cap, as well as amount of revenue generated by these companies have been in comparison and a part of big discussions among the analysts and considered primary competitors in China’s e-commerce space.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>JD emerging in Asia and America:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>JD has emerged as a business giant in the e-commerce industry. According to various business analysts across the globe, they believe that the consumer ship is back in China. Not only that, big businesses will be coming to China in the coming years, which will help the Chinese economy to re-establish; and the sudden boost in business coming from big countries like New York and Hong Kong is a positive sign after the pandemic. The total amount of business expected is nearly $12.02 billion within a few months of 2021, which is about to increase to about 8.9percent by the end of this year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>JD subsidiaries going public:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The subsidiaries of JD’s business lie in 4 different categories that have emerged as strong contenders are helping the company to grow quickly.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The first one is Logistics; i.e. the company’s delivery unit, giving a boost of about $3.2 billion to the company.&nbsp;</li><li>The second subsidiary that has given the maximum amount of profit to<strong> </strong>the company is Health, in which the medicines are sold online enabling an almost $4 billion rise in Hong Kong.&nbsp;</li><li>The third subsidiary is the parent company itself that has raised a total amount of $4.5 billion within no time, benefiting the company users in Hong Kong and the USA.&nbsp;</li><li>The fourth one- the foremost subsidiary is related to Grocery delivery which was the biggest strategic investor and gained about $320 million accounting to be the main factor through which the maximum amount of business got generated.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All of the aforementioned factors have supported the company in reaching the market cap of almost $198 billion, according to data research companies and this will keep increasing with time, giving tough competition to Alibaba in the future, making JD.com the next e-commerce giant of the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Alibaba’s rival may surpass it in the e-commerce space', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Business,Currency Market,Social Media', '1623067648_markus-winkler-nrWBAm69fLo-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:07:28'),
(102, 'hsbc-selling-off-its-shares-in-the-market', 'Tue, 01 Jun 2021 12:54:19 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over the years, various banks have jumped into the banking industry. Where many of them have established themselves profoundly in the market with their unique features and facilities, many disappeared. Banks like Barclays and Citi Bank have gained fame over the years but as soon as the bank started facing difficulties in gaining business, the founders thought to close the chapter and their existence vanished from the face of the earth.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HSBC is also one of those banks with its unique features and the famous tagline of the <em>world’s local bank</em> that expanded with immense popularity around the globe. People from across the globe started investing blindly into this bank and within no time this bank was famous around the globe. There was no country where HSBC had not established its branch. This bank that started in Asia, set a benchmark in the United Kingdom, and gradually moved out of Europe. The investors were not only providing the business but giving the maximum amount in shares. But, with the passage of time, the value of HSBC in the market started decreasing because of the increasing competition in the banking sector.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Winding up of HSBC in the United Kingdom:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the increasing banking market in the UK, a downfall was seen in the business of HSBC. The local investors started to back off from HSBC that resulted in a huge loss; of around 17.3%. This decrement in the market capacity pushed the country managers to take a big step of shutting off their business. While UK was considered as the hub of HSBC, winding up the business from there and diminishing caused various trepidations for which they were not ready. Closing the business abruptly put a big question on their performance and caused a huge depression in the global market cap. At this point, some radical and rational steps were required so as to avoid a big loss.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Reason for selling off of the branches</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HSBC wanted to focus more on its business in the Asian countries, and the US retail business coming from the Europe-based banks was not enough. This was giving a major loss to the bank and as the competition was increasing in Europe; as with Goldman Sachs and JP Morgan Chase, it was getting difficult for all the branches to maintain the market cap and compete with the increasing trends. Thus, in order to cater all the issues, the CEO of HSBC Noel Quinn came to a decision of selling off its branches to some local banks. The bank will be selling off 80 of its East Coast branches to the Citizen Banks and the next 10 west coast branches to the Cathay Bank, where all the deposits and investments will be transferred to these banks. The other 20 to 25 branches will be converted into wealth management centers, and the rest of the remaining branches will be closed. While this was a difficult step, it has been for the betterment of the bank. According to the statement released by the company officials, the focus will be on the Asian region from now onwards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'HSBC selling off its shares in the market', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Stockwatch', '1623067619_sophie-louisnard-ZPToLP10wQI-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:06:59'),
(103, 'bitcoin-damages-further-increased-by-8-it-s-time-for-bears-to-rule', 'Tue, 01 Jun 2021 12:59:14 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitcoin is going through a difficult time. The king of cryptocurrencies has fallen and investors are worried about its future. Bitcoin was flying high up in the air a month ago. Experts had predicted a new world record at $100000 but unfortunately, these predictions turned out to be quite unrealistic at the end. It is true that Bitcoin had been moving towards this mark but sudden changes in the market lead to a huge fall from the top.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitcoin is right now trading in the $30000s level and is expected to crash further before making a rebound. But the question here is that wouldn’t that be too late for the Bulls?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The rise of bitcoin took it to the highest peak and now that it has fallen by more than $30000, the Bulls are in deep trouble. In a recent announcement it was revealed that thousands of small investors have gone bankrupt due to the sudden change of events. And the Bitcoin losing streak is expected to continue in June. This is good news for the bears that have been maximizing their benefits since the last few weeks but the Bulls are deep under water!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bitcoin latest development&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Chinese step to crackdown and the increased awareness about the environment has pushed down BTC to its lowest this month. If we look at the bigger picture, Bitcoin has declined by a huge margin of 40% in value and this gap is expected to widen even more in June. The expected fall is predicted to touch the 50% mark and that is what is troubling investors right now.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitcoin losses increased by 8.2% today and it is now trading at $35339. The king of crypto has been smashed to the ground with no escape in sight. The previous periods losses accumulated to 6.2% which shows how consistently it has been falling with every passing day.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrik Lykke, executive director of ARK36 explained this movement in the following words:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Bitcoin is currently in a bit of ‘slumber mode’ trading in the range of $34000 and $40000”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrik’s statement shows an optimistic view that predicts a comeback for the King. This may be true in future but for now the BTC seems to be stuck in the bear’s den. If we look at the facts, Bitcoin has already lost 37% value in the month of May. If these losses continue to increase, Bitcoin will be at the lowest point since September 2011.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why is Bitcoin falling?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitcoin was rising to a point which would’ve made it unbeatable in the crypto world. Unfortunately, the timing of this rise was not ideal. China recently announced a crackdown against anyone who was involved in Bitcoin mining. Their reasons were quite clear; waste of resources was not an option for them. While this had damaging the position of Bitcoin already, Tesla founder, Elon Musk announced that they were no longer going to be accepting payments in Bitcoin.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The two announcements from the two different parts of the world proved to be damaging for Bitcoin. Investors lost confidence and the rest is history. Bitcoin came crashing down to the point which was not expected at all.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The King of crypto is expected to rise later again in July but till then, the Bears are in complete control. For more such articles, keep visiting our website and don’t forget to subscribe before leaving!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bitcoin damages further increased by 8% - It’s time for Bears to rule!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Crypto Mining News,Currency Market', '1623067563_aleksi-raisa-LYhMnce2czE-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:06:03'),
(104, 'your-next-step-top-3-stocks-to-trade', 'Tue, 01 Jun 2021 13:01:11 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today we are going to shed some light on the stocks that you can trade. A lot of attention is being circling around the top stocks in the market lately. The stocks we are going to talk about today are showing bullish trends therefore, keep reading to explore more!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Looking upon the trends of the stock market, we see a it is blooming because of an increase in the opportunities. Traders are making use of these opportunities and exploring them to the fullest. There has been volatility in the stock market due to the doings of the reddit group Wall Street Bets. There is no doubt in saying that you will most likely be uncertain because of these ups and downs in the trends which leads to unsure situations and decisions of what to trade.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>GOOGL</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s start with GOOGL Alphabet. There was some volatility seen in the initial period but later on it shows a strong and solid start of the company. It is safe to say that an increase in the share price of the company has been increasing since the past several weeks. Not only growing but the it has been speeded up since February.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now you must be thinking what could be causing this trend? The answer is simple and it is the Q4 earnings by the company. It strengthens the company\'s position. Most companies were seen to be struggling ever since the pandemic hit but this one made a revenue of $46.20 billion from the California based tech giant ad.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is simple if you look deeper into the trends. Now the pandemic worse effects have been calmed and things are getting better so it is certain that the stocks would even show a brighter picture, the revenues will raise even more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Netflix&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Up next we have Netflix, another name that does not need any introduction. 2020 has been hard on majority of the companies out there but it is safe to say Netflix was not in that list. 204 million subscribers is not a small number and it is only growing in the 190 countries. Their main game is revolving around the number of subscribers. Netflix financials are promising and show a solid position according to the analysts that the company will most certainly go for share buybacks and will finally cease fund borrowing for daily expenditure. So another stock to trade is right here&nbsp; you can now Netflix and chill!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tesla</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next we have none other than the very famous Tesla, Inc. A little background - A company that came into being in 2003 in California. It is not only a mega electric vehicle company but also intends contribution in the clean energy sector. The products it is currently producing are energy storage, electric cars, solar roof tiles and solar panels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is above its competitors for this very reason as well and the product range will only increase in the near future. Looking back at the past 1 year, Tesla has been performing excellently. One year later the company is at a rise of 375% which is immaculate because last year it was trading at 171.68 USD while this year it is at 816.12 USD. This alone is a huge yes yes for you to trade right here. Know that it has a current secure BEV market of 16% and that is certainly amazing potential. The total sales are also likely to grow to 11.2 million, another hit. By 2030, be sure it will be somehwere around 31.1 million.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Your next step- top 3 stocks to trade', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Stockwatch', '1623067527_adeolu-eletu-E7RLgUjjazc-unsplash (2).jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:05:27'),
(105, 'gold-climbs-8-as-bulls-join-the-party', 'Tue, 01 Jun 2021 13:08:50 +0000', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gold is finally showing signs of a bullish trend and the bears are not happy about it. The king of metals was under bearish influence last week but bulls are back in the game now. Gold is on another bullish streak and Friday proved to be a lucky breakthrough for it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The yellow metal is once again trading above $1900 as the month of May is coming to an end. This has been the best month for gold if we look at the yearly chart, which shows an approximate gain of 8% in May. The previous 10 months had been tough for gold and the bears have been dominant throughout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, as we move towards June, gold seems to be traveling towards a bullish path. It is now time for the bulls to take control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The bigger picture</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It has been a decent week for gold and the future outlook now seems to be positive. Having said that, there are various reasons behind this sudden upward movement that should be noted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ed Moya, analyst at OANDA described this bullish movement in the following words:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Bullion had a good week and while the rally appears to be taking a break, it seems it might only be a temporary one.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Ed Moya\'s statement is a little too early to consider, he has a point. If we look at the past trends, the graph is expected to move in a downwards direction soon. The upward movement seems like a short term reaction of market triggered by the bullish investors.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The true test for gold will be after the next couple of months of hot inflation reports and if we have some surprising better-than-expected non-farm payroll reports.\" Moya further added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now here\'s the important part. Covid has destroyed economies, inflation is high and the world is in recovery. The inflation reports will actually decide the future direction of gold trading. Hence, the current bullish trend might not be easy to control by the bulls.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we talk about the Personal Consumption Expenditure report of 2021, the readings till April were not in favor of the bulls in any way. The data revealed showed a 3.6% jump in inflation and this became a major reason for the gold downfall noticed 2 months ago.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The future expected readings are also expected to go higher, in which case, gold will see another downfall in the months of July and August.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Right now the PCE readings have helped the gold in damage control caused by the bears. PCE is basically a hedge against inflation so an improvement in PCE means a boosted investor confidence. The current position of gold in the market is due the the latest PCE readings, which is again why some analysts have been calling it a short term trend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our analysis shows a bullish June for gold followed by a bearish July and August. For more interesting articles, keep visiting our website. Don\'t forget to subscribe before leaving!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Gold climbs 8% as Bulls join the party!', NULL, 'Published', NULL, 'Gold,Hot Updates,News &amp; Updates', '1623067478_matt-flores-NpgN1gXdlSw-unsplash.jpg', NULL, '2021-06-07 07:04:38'),
